Commentary: Kasun Rajitha begins with a gentle loosener full and wide outside off. Usman Khawaja happy to let this one go through to the keeper.
There is some shape for the bowler as his serves this wide from off stump on a good length. Usman Khawaja lets it go once again.
Slightly full this time and angling into the stumps from outside off, Usman Khawaja knocks this towards mid off.
On a good length angling into off, Usman Khawaja fends this towards point.
Good-length delivery but really wide from the stump. Usman Khawaja leaves this for the wicket-keeper who is really sloppy and doesn't get hold of the ball. Concedes a bye in the process.
Wide once again from Kasun Rajitha on a good length. David Warner also leaves this one.

Really well played! Yet again, Usman Khawaja makes excellent use of the crease which is the key when playing on rank turners. Flatter and on off, Khawaja goes right back and defends it right under his eyes.
A little too quicker again and on off, Khawaja goes back and pushes it to covers. No turn seen on the first two balls for Mendis.

Now bowls this one very short and outside off, Khawaja hangs back and pushes it through covers for one. He gets off the mark. This was the problem for Lanka in the last game, they failed to bowl 6 good balls in an over.
A little bit of turn as the pace was quite good on this ball. Slows it up, gives it air and lands it on off, Warner pushes it towards cover and takes one.

Turn and bounce! Yet again, gives it air, lands it on off and gets it to spin away and also bounce extra. Khawaja plays it really well as he defends it by taking one hand off the handle to keep it down on the ground.
Two more! Deft! Shorter and outside off, Khawaja waits, plays it late and through short third man. Two taken.

FOUR! The first boundary for Australia and as expected comes from the bat of David Warner! Kasun Rajitha serves this wide from off stump and slightly full, David Warner finds the gap through cover-point and times the ball towards the boundary!
Kasun Rajitha goes closer to the stumps on a good length. David Warner fends this down the pitch.
Pull his length back a fraction but stays just outside off, David Warner defends this back to the bowler.
Kasun Rajitha serves this a little wider and fuller, David Warner gets a stride forward and fends this towards point.
Kasun Rajitha has come back well in this over after the first ball. On a good length just outside off, David Warner gets well forward and defends it back to Kasun Rajitha.
This one is pitched up and delivered outside off, David Warner playing within himself as he defends this solidly!

FOUR! That is a brilliant shot! Excellent use of the feet. Gets to the pitch of it as he sees Mendis toss it up and slams it over mid on for a boundary. Yet again, the use of the feet is very important on such wickets.
Now he plays this right off the back foot. Mendis bowls this quicker and shorter, probably because of the last ball. Khawaja goes right back and defends.
Really well bowled! Khawaja steps out and that is spotted by Mendis. He shortens the length a little and it is blocked.

That is tinder really well again. Mendis is probably worried about Khawaja coming down the wicket and hence, pushes it through and on the pads, Khawaja rocks back and whips it through square leg for two.
A little too flat again and on off, not a lot of turn or zip off the surface so far. Khawaja quite easily rocks back and defends.
Better from Mendis! This is what he needs to be bowling. Tosses it up, nice and slow. Draws Khawaja forward and hoping the ball could do its bit. This one goes on with the arm and Khawaja defends.
Great delivery from Kasun Rajitha! Gets the ball to come in from around the wicket and straighten off the pitch. David Warner feels for the ball and gets beaten.
On a good length just outside off, David Warner goes back in his crease and fends it off his back foot.
Full and angled into middle from outside off, David Warner plays this back towards the bowler who collects and feigns a throw, back towards the batter.
Slightly full and angled into the pads, David Warner works this towards square leg and looks for a single that is not there.

OUT! TIMBER! That is a beauty, an absolute beauty! We have seen Warner being dismissed in that manner several times to Broad in England and now it is Kasun Rajitha who does it here. He continues his good form. This is angled into the middle pole from around the wicket. Warner does the right thing, he looks to play the original trajectory on a wicket which is not doing a lot. This ball though lands and then moves away. Warner is beaten all ends up as he tries to defend, it goes past the outside edge and hits the stumps. Probably Warner could have played that with a forward stride but he decided to play it off the back foot and that is what proved to be his downfall. Early wicket for the hosts, perfect start for them. Yet another low score in this part of the world for Warner. Marnus Labuschagne walks out to bat now!
Good-length from Kasun Rajitha as he delivers this outside off, Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one! A successful over for Sri Lanka as it is a wicket maiden!
Flatter, yet again worried about Khawaja coming down the track but this is not the pace Lanka will be happy with. Khawaja hangs back and defends.
FOUR! Deft yet again! Just used the pace of the bowler there. Mendis is quite happy to fire the ball in. Khawaja has no qualms to go back and then guide it down to the third man fence.

Mendis has gotten away with one there! Not sure why he is looking to push it through. Yes, he is worried about Khawaja coming down the track but this pace is a lot easier to play for Khawaja. This time though it beats his edge but it was not the best of balls. Short and outside off, Khawaja rocks back and looks to cut but misses.
Darts this slightly shorter and on off, Khawaja defends.
Better! Nice and slow, gives it air, draws the batter forward but Khawaja negotiates it well.
Two decent deliveries to end! Floats it up and on off, Khawaja lunges forward and defends.
Marnus Labuschagne is off the mark. Kasun Rajitha goes full and angles this in from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne guides this towards mid-wicket with the angle and gets a single.
'Round the wicket to the left-hander, Kasun Rajitha serves this wide from a good length. Usman Khawaja not interested to play at it.
Similar deliver and getting good shape away. Usman Khawaja is being patient as he lets this one through as well.
Usman Khawaja leaves the ball once again, Kasun Rajitha gets the ball closer to the stumps but still wide enough to allow the batter to not play at it.
Kasun Rajitha serves this full just outside off, Usman Khawaja finally plays a shot as he drives this firmly towards covers.
Kasun Rajitha back to bowling outside off on a good length, and Usman Khawaja back to shouldering his arms to it.
Tosses this up and lands it on middle, Marnus Labuschagne blocks.
A little bit of turn but since the length is short, Marnus Labuschagne has enough time to go back and work it to mid-wicket.
A single now! Slightly shorter and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it through mid-wicket and takes one.

FOUR! Very good, very, very good from Khawaja! He has used the sweeps to great effect. This time he goes down on one knee and just paddle sweeps it fine on the leg side, uses the pace of the ball and bags a boundary.
Tosses it up but bowls it way too full and on middle, it is worked down to long on for one.
Gives it air and lands it on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends. Yet again a good delivery to end but he needs to bowl such deliveries on consistent basis.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off stump, Usman Khawaja rises on his toes and lets it go through to the keeper.
Kasun Rajitha attacks the stumps this time on a good length, Usman Khawaja plays this straight back to the left of the stumps as it is collected by the mid on fielder.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Usman Khawaja goes on his back foot and punches this towards cover.

What a brilliant delivery! Kasun Rajitha has his tail up here as he bowls an unplayable delivery to Usman Khawaja. 'Round the wicket goes wide from the crease and pitches it a fraction short on off. Gets the ball to keep its line and beats Usman Khawaja all ends up!
Good response from Usman Khawaja! Kasun Rajitha goes full now angling the ball into off stump, Usman Khawaja plays this straight past the mid on fielder for a couple of runs.
Kasun Rajitha goes full outside off, Usman Khawaja was ready and hits it well towards the off side but finds the cover fielder.
Flatter and on off, Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and defends.
Slightly shorter and around off, Marnus Labuschagne guides it to point.
Yet again this one is played off the back foot, it is on middle, blocked.
Ramesh makes the mistake of bowling this short again, on middle, Marnus Labuschagne stays back and works it through square leg for one.
This is what Sri Lanka will want Ramesh Mendis to bowl. Even Niroshan Dickwella enjoyed that. Tosses it up, gets it to drift back in from outside off. Khawaja is drawn forward but he plays it well.
Shorter and on off, Khawaja guides it through point for one. Yet again goes short on the very lsat ball. Easy for Khawaja.
NO BALL! Kasun Rajitha goes over the wicket now to the southpaw but has not got his run-up right as he over-steps. Full and on middle, Usman Khawaja defends this solidly.
Back-of-a-length now and angling away from the left-hander, Usman Khawaja leaves this one alone.
Full once again and on the pads, easy picking for Usman Khawaja who works this towards square leg for a brace.
Goes shorter in length but still on the pads. Usman Khawaja happy to work this off his legs towards square leg for two more runs.
Kasun Rajitha decides to change the angle and goes 'round the wicket once again. Delivers this on a good length attacking the off pole, Usman Khawaja gets a stride forward and looks firm in defense.
This one is wide from the stumps and on a good length. Usman Khawaja watches it go past for the keeper to collect.
Bangs this in short and angles it into the batter. Usman Khawaja rises up and plays it down towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, Marnus Labuschagne styays back and defends.
Angled into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne works it through square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, blocked.
That spun, spun big! This is tossed up on off, it lands and then spins away. Khawaja lunges and looks to defend but is beaten. Really good pace there, it was nice and slow.

Just short, a misfield and a run! Mendis looks to push it through again, he bowls it shorter and outside off, Khawaja cuts uppishly but it lands short of point who does not stop it cleanly. A single in the end.
Not quite got the length right to the right-hander. Goes short again, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Maheesh Theekshana begins with a full delivery angling into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne comes down the wicket to negate the turn and plays it towards deep square leg for a single.
This one is full and outside off, Usman Khawaja knocks this to deep cover for a single.
Full delivery turning in from off, Marnus Labuschagne uses his wrists and clips it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Maheesh Theekshana flights this one outside off and gets it to turn a bit. Usman Khawaja guides this towards the cover fielder.
Full once again and angled in from outside off. Usman Khawaja gets forward and blocks it towards short cover.
Slightly back of a length and turning towards the leg stump, Usman Khawaja goes back in the crease and works this towards backward square leg for a single to retain strike.
Tossed up on middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Gives it nice amount of air and lands it on off, it is driven through covers for one.
Quicker and on off, Marnus Labuschagne stays back and defends it.
Turn and bounce! Flatter and outside off, this one lands and spins back in a long way. Marnus Labuschagne goes back and looks to flick but gets hit on the arm.
Another one which is quicker and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to short leg.
Two more! Shorter in length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it through covers for a couple.
Maheesh Theekshana fires this one full and on middle, Usman Khawaja gets his bat down and fends it towards short cover.
Flights this a bit and bowls it full on middle once again. Usman Khawaja is happy to defend these deliveries on the stump as he fends it towards cover.
Wide this time from off stump and slightly short, Usman Khawaja goes back in his crease and Slashes it towards deep cover-point for a single.
Marnus Labuschagne using his feet against spin here. Full delivery in line with the stumps, the batter gets down the pitch and works it to long on for another single.
Maheesh Theekshana serves this one a little too full and outside off, Usman Khawaja places this past the cover fielder to rotate the strike.
Back-of-a-length delivery turning in from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne uses the crease and goes back to work this through mid-wicket and retains the strike for the next over.
Nicely tossed up and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
A single now! On middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it through mid-wicket for one.
Another one tossed up and on middle, Khawaja keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, Khawaja hangs back and keeps it out.
Pushes this one through and lands it on off, Usman Khawaja stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Good delivery to begin as he pitches this in line with the stumps and gets Marnus Labuschagne to defend straight back down the pitch.
Floats this one into the batter from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne plays a defensive shot but gets an inside edge past short fine leg for a couple of runs.
Full and turning in from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne is being watchful as he smothers it down into the pitch.

Quicker delivery served slightly short but gets sharp turn from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes back to cut but gets cramped for space as he just about manages to keep the ball from shattering his stumps.
Full and slightly wide from off stump. Marnus Labuschagne defends this well back to the bowler.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this one full and angling down leg, Marnus Labuschagne works this to fine leg for a single. Good over to start off from Prabath Jayasuriya!
Angled into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne works it through square leg and takes one.
Floats it up and lands it on off, kept out.
Flatter and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Loopy ball on off, Usman Khawaja leans forward and pushes it to mid off.
Shorter and outside off, Khawaja guides it to point.
Caresses it nicely! Shorter and around off, Usman Khawaja goes back and guides it past point for two.
Tosses this one full on leg and gets it to turn and keep the line, Marnus Labuschagne fends this towards mid on.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this to the right of the bowler and is collected by mid on fielder.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne clobbers this one to the boundary! Prabath Jayasuriya goes way too full on middle, Marnus Labuschagne Gets on his knees and powers the sweep wide of deep square leg for a boundary!
Full once again outside off and stays low, Marnus Labuschagne defends this with soft hands.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over and it is an action replay! Prabath Jayasuriya needs to adjust his length as he delivers this one full as well and gets it to pitch in line with the middle stump. Marnus Labuschagne repeats the sweep shot and gets better connection this time as it flies to the deep square leg boundary!
Prabath Jayasuriya has been too full this over as this on pitches outside off. Marnus Labuschagne happy to defend this as 8 runs have already come off this over.
Flatter and on off, kept out.
On the stumps, defended.

FOUR! Too short and put away! The fifty-run stand is up between the two and it has taken Australia in a decent position after the loss of Warner. Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Quicker and on off, defended.
On the stumps again, blocked.
Tosses it up on middle, this is played to mid on.
Adjusts his length to start this over, Goes a fraction shorter outside off, Marnus Labuschagne has to fend this towards the off side.

That is more like what we would want to see from the Sri Lankan spinners! Prabath Jayasuriya keeps this slightly short and pitching on middle, gets the ball to turn sharply from the wicket and beat Marnus Labuschagne's outside edge!
Quicker delivery bowled full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne mistimes his shot towards the cover fielder.
Prabath Jayasuriya bowls full now and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne opens the face of the bat and works it past point for a single.
Goes over the wicket to the left-hander and pulls the length back a bit. Delivers this wide from off stump and Usman Khawaja does not play at it.
Full delivery wide outside off, Usman Khawaja steps towards the ball and leaves it alone.
On off, this is driven to mid off for one.
On off, defended.
Another one tossed up on off, Usman Khawaja pushes it to covers.
Floats it up and lands it on off, it is pushed to covers.

OUT! TIMBER! That is yet anothe beauty of a delivery and Australia break the partnership that was looking at ease! Ramesh Mendis gets his first. Khawaja walks back 13 short of a half ton. He is shell-shocked. He just does not want to walk off. This is flatter, it lands on middle, Khawaja goes back and looks to defend. The ball though turns enough, it goes past the outside edge and then hits the top of off. Mendis is ecstatic and that is a huge wicket. Can Sri Lanka now get one more at least before Lunch?
Smith wastes no time in getting off the mark! On the pads, this is tucked around the corner for one.
Good delivery from Prabath Jayasuriya as he bowls this full and angles it into the stumps. Steven Smith comes forward and defends firmly.
Quicker delivery angling in from outside off, Steven Smith gets forward again but drives this one towards cover.
Similar delivery but closer to the stumps. Steven Smith is happy to defend this one towards the off side.
FOUR! Steven Smith goes down the wicket and attacks a full delivery on middle stump! Uses his wrists in trademark fashion as he lofts the ball towards deep square leg for his first boundary!
Full delivery attacking the stumps from outside off, Steven Smith showing us some solid front foot defense.
Full once again and aimed for the stumps, Steven Smith firmly knocks it back towards the bowler.
A single as this is worked through mid-wicket.
Down the leg side. Left alone.
Shorter and on middle, defended.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
On middle, this one turns back in. Smith looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
A lot of turn and bounce! On the pads, this one spins away and also takes off. Smith leaves it alone. Dickwella collects it well.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne uses his wrists and taps it towards short leg.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this full and outside off. There is no turn and gets the outside half of Marnus Labuschagne's bat and goes towards point.
Full once again outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets a stride forward and defends.
Full delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne uses the sweep shot to drag the ball towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
Full delivery outside off, Steven Smith covers the line of the delivery and fends it towards cover.
Prabath Jayasuriya continues bowling full and outside off, Steven Smith comes to the offside and uses his wrists to work it towards mid-wicket for a single and will keep strike.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Smith works it through square leg for one.

STUMPING CHANCE MISSED! Niroshan Dickwella did miss a few in the first game which proved to be costly and he misses one here again. Marnus Labuschagne gets a life and that is probably the kind of luck one needs when he is out of form! Can he make use of it now? He steps out, this is tossed up outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to play it on the off side but more towards point. He misses but Dickwella fails to collect the ball. There was a little extra bounce but one would expect Dickwella to collect that.
Shorter and on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Another one on the shorter side, this is flicked to mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
Starts off with a loose delivery wide from off stump, gets a shade of swing from a good length. Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne is not going to miss out on the short delivery every time! Kasun Rajitha has not got his line correct as he bowls this wide and Marnus Labuschagne reaches for it and wacks it through cover-point for a boundary! Marnus Labuschagne looks like he wants the make the most of his lifeline!
Serves this one a good length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne watchful as he leaves teh ball alone.
Kasun Rajitha gets good swing from a good length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne chooses to shoulder his arms to this one as well.

Back-of-a-length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes for the pull but does not rise as much as he would have expected. Gets hit on the back thigh and the ball goes to the slip fielder who seems to be claiming a catch!

FOUR! A boundary to start and a boundary to end the over! Kasun Rajitha has got his line and length all over the place in this over. This one is wide from off stump and a fraction short, Marnus Labuschagne does not try to power this as he places it in the gap between cover and point for another boundary!
Quite awkwardly played in the end! This is angled into middle, this one holds its line. Smith looks to defend it but in a strange manner, it goes off the outside edge towards short third man for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Another single! On the pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Tosses it up on middle, Smith works it down to mid on.
A little too straight, Smith pads it away.
A dot to end! Flatter and on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Kasun Rajitha starts this over a fraction full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone.

Pulls the length back, and angles it in from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne rises on his toes and works it wide of mid-wicket. Should have been just one but some ordinary fielding allows the batters to take three runs.
On a good length, wide from off stump, Steven Smith goes for the cut but is not short enough and mistimes it towards the point fielder.
On a good length outside off, Steven Smith fends this back towards Kasun Rajitha.
Serves this full outside off, Steven Smith moves in his crease and goes to the offside to fend this towards mid on.
Full once again and attacks the stumps this time, Steven Smith defends this firmly back down the pitch.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
A single as this is worked through mid-wicket.

FOUR! That is easy! With hardly any fielder on the off side, that is a gift. Mendis gives it a lot of air, Smith straightaway steps out and makes it into a full toss, it is creamed through covers for a boundary.
Now follows the boundary with a single as this is pushed down to long on for one.

Close! Marnus Labuschagne probably misreads the length there! Flatter and on middle, this one is fractionally full. Marnus Labuschagne stays back in his crease but gets his bat down in time. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Steven Smith gets the scoreboard moving straight after the break. Kasun Rajitha serves this full outside off, Steven Smith plays this to extra cover and takes a single.
Good-length delivery just outside off, nips back in a fraction and gets the inside edge of Marnus Labuschagne's bat onto his pads as he tries to defend the ball.
NO BALL! Kasun Rajitha bowls a good-length delivery on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends this back to the bowler. The third umpire lets them know that the bowler has over-stepped.
On a good length once agin outside off, Marnus Labuschagne works this wide of cover for a single.
Strays down leg from a good length, Steven Smith tries to glance this but misses and goes through to the keeper.
Goes fuller now outside off, Steven Smith defends this back down the pitch.
Similar delivery bowled full but a tad outside off, Steven Smith defends this towards cover.
Ramesh Mendis starts of back of a length and turns this into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne glances it with the angle towards backward square leg for a single.
Full and angling down leg, Steven Smith goes back on his crease and plays it to the right of short leg.
Full once again on off, Steven Smith is staying back in his crease as he plays it down into the pitch.
Steven Smith comes down the wicket and meets the ball on the full to defend in back to the bowler.
Tossed up full and angling in, Steven Smith defends this towards short mid on.
Serves this back of a length and down leg, Steven Smith works this towards backward square leg. One run from the over for Ramesh Mendis right after Lunch.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Yet another one on a length and around off, Marnus Labuschagne plays it right under his eyes.

A loud appeal from the bowler but he was the only one doing so. Going down leg easily! On the pads, Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick but misses, it hits the pad, a loud shout but turned down. It goes towards fine leg. Two leg byes taken.
Another one on a length and around off, Marnus Labuschagne guides it to point.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Angled into the off pole, Smith pushes it to mid off.
Flatter and on off, this one turns back in. Defended.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
Quicker and on the stumps, blocked.
Uppish but safe! Tossed up on middle, Marnus Labuschagne lunges and looks to defend, it hits the splice but goes well away from the short leg fielder.
On middle, this is worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Marnus steps out and pushes this to mid off. A maiden.
Kamindu Mendis serves this full and angling in from outside off, Steven Smith covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Strays down leg stump from a good length. Steven Smith raises his hands and leaves the ball alone.
Good-length delivery outside off, Steven Smith guides this to the cover fielder and shouts NO loudly.
Kamindu Mendis bowling on a good length outside off. Steven Smith plays this with soft hands towards cover.
Slower delivery this time delivered full and in line with off stump. Steven Smith waits on the ball and taps it back to Kasun Rajitha.
Goes a fraction fuller outside off, Steven Smith knocks this to the left of the bowler. Two maidens on the trot!
Marnus Labuschagne gets down the wicket and catches the ball on the full. Manages to knock it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and punches it wide of mid off for a run.
Full and angling into the pads, Steven Smith flicks this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Ramesh Mendis pulls his length back and turns this in from outside off, Steven Smith goes back and defends it down into the pitch.
Shorter delivery with big turn as it pitches on off and goes down leg, Steven Smith plays this fine past backward square leg for a single.
Full and attacking the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne shows good wrist work to guide this towards backward square leg for a single.
On off, defended.
FOUR! Pulled away! That was not that short but put away nicely! Short and on middle, this is hit through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Another one on the off pole, kept out.
On off, kept out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Ramesh Mendis goes full and turns it into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne nudges this towards backward square leg.

FOUR! Poor delivery from Ramesh Mendis! Pitches this one short on leg and keeps going down with the angle. Marnus Labuschagne does not miss out as he pulls this to the fine leg boundary for four runs!

FOUR! Back-to back boundaries for Marnus Labuschagne! Ramesh Mendis is way too short and compensates in line by bowling outside off. Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and thumps it through covers for another boundary! Runs coming far too quickly for Australia!
Goes fuller now but on leg, Marnus Labuschagne sweeps this firmly to short fine leg and another misfield allows the batters to take a single.
FOUR! Three in the over and Steven Smith contributes with one! Full on leg once again and Steven Smith is on his knees to sweep this hard towards deep square leg for four more runs!
Full and angled into the pads, Steven Smith fends this towards mid on. 13 runs of the over!
Flatter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Fires it on the stumps, kept out.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, kept out well again. Not a lot of turn for the left-arm spinner.
Floats it up and bowls it on off, this is pushed to covers.

Really good! On a wicket where there is not a lot happening, change of pace is important. This is flatter and quicker on middle, Marnus Labuschagne plays a risky shot as he strokes it through covers for two.
Maheesh Theekshana goes wide and bowls it short. Steven Smith is up for it and plays it through cover-point for a brace.
Serves this full and angling into the stumps. Steven Smith defends this back to the bowler.
That is a good length to bowl outside off, Steven Smith fends this towards cover.
Slightly shorter outside off, Steven Smith comes forward to negate the turn and defends well.
Full-length delivery turning into the pads, Steven Smith plays this to the left of the short-leg fielder.
Full once again on off, Steven Smith taps this down towards short leg.

FOUR! This one is close! Seems to be Marnus Labuschagne's day so far! Full delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes for the sweep and gets a thick under edge that goes just past the off pole.  Goes under the keeper's glove for a boundary to long leg.
FOUR! That is beautiful! The last boundary was a streaky one but this was a wonderful stroke! Steps out, gets to the pitch of it and creams it through covers.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
On off again, slightly fuller, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to covers.
On middle, this is blocked.
Another one on the stumps, it is kept out well.
Full outside off, stays a fraction low and Marnus Labuschagne defends with soft hands.
Full and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne defends this back to Maheesh Theekshana.
Full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets a stride forward and defends it towards cover.
Marnus Labuschagne comes down the wicket and flicks the full delivery outside  off towards long on for a single.
Full and on middle stump, defended back to the bowler.
Full toss outside off, Steven Smith can not get it away as he hits it straight to the cover fielder.
Flights this full onto the pads, Marnus Labuschagne guides this to mid-wicket.
Pulls the length back a bit on middle, Marnus Labuschagne works this to mid-wicket as well.
Full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne hits this well towards short cover.
Slightly short and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne can not find the gap in the offside as it is stopped by the cover fielder.
Quicker delivery angled in onto the pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this to backward square leg for a single.
Back-of-a-length and angled onto the pads, Steven Smith guides this past square leg to retain strike.
Angled into the pads, this is worked towards square leg for one.
Marnus Labuschagne steps out and works it through mid-wicket for one.
Another one angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one more.
On middle, this is played to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, kept out.
Fires it on off, Smith plays it onto the ground.
Flights this full on leg, Marnus Labuschagne moves his front foot out of the way and hits it to the cover fielder.
Goes short this time outside off, Marnus Labuschagne guides this towards point.
Tossed up full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets a firm hit towards cover.
Marnus Labuschagne comes forward and hits the full delivery outside off towards mid off and rushes across for a quick single.
FOUR! Lovely use of the wrist from Steven Smith! Full delivery angled into the pads, Steven Smith flicks this past mid-wicket and the ball rushes to the fence for a boundary!
Full and in line with the stumps, fended towards short mid on.
Full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne this to the right of the Maheesh Theekshana who dives and stops the ball.
Full and straight, Marnus Labuschagne taps this down towards mid-wicket.
Quicker delivery angled into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this past short leg towards the deep for a single.
Full and turning in from outside off, Steven Smith drags this towards mid on with the turn and takes a run.
Carrom ball delivered back of a length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this from inside the crease.
Shorter delivery angled into the leg stump, Marnus Labuschagne goes back and flicks this past short leg for another run and keeps strike.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne is looking really dangerous! Short delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne uses the depth of the crease to go back and thump this through covers for a boundary right after the break!
Follows it up with a single. Full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne works this to covers to rotate the strike.

FOUR! Steven Smith joins the party! Full delivery on middle stump, Steven Smith charges down the pitch and hits it straight to the right of the bowler. Beats the mid on fielder as it rushes to the long on boundary!
Full and drifting into the batter from outside off, Steven Smith defends this to short cover.
Quicker delivery angling in from outside off. Steven Smith hits this firmly to short cover.
Full and angled into the pads, Steven Smith flicks this watchfully towards short mid-wicket.
Gets drift away from the batter as he bowls this full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne feels for it and gets beaten.
Loops this full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne works this past cover for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Steven Smith hits this hard and finds the cover fielder.
Full and turning in from outside off, Steven Smith gets forward and defends solidly.
Short this time and with some width outside off, Steven Smith cuts this to deep backward point for a single.
Goes 'round the wicket for the last ball and pitches this full onto the pads. Marnus Labuschagne guides this towards square leg for a single.
Nicely bowled! This angles into the middle pole, Marnus Labuschagne makes room and then pushes it to covers.
Shorter and around off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it through covers and takes two.
Marnus steps out and pushes this towards mid off and takes a quick run.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, kept out.
On the stumps, defended.
Full delivery to begin, outside off, Steven Smith knocks this towards mid off.
Full and angled in from outside off, Steven Smith wrists this towards long on for a single.
Outside off stump line and full, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Maheesh Theekshana goes shorter angling it into the pads, Marnus Labuschagne goes back in the crease a gets a single through square leg.
Full delivery on off, Steven Smith defends this back towards the bowler.
Full and in line with the stumps, Steven Smith hits the straight past the diving Maheesh Theekshana to long on for a single.
Full and angled into the pads, Steven Smith works this leg side and gets the short mid-wicket fielder to dive to his left and stop the ball.
Shortish and on off, this is pushed to covers again.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
This is worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Another single as this is nudged on the leg side.
Short and on the pads, Smith plays it on the leg side for one.
Kasun Rajitha begins bowling full angled into the pads, Steven Smith works this towards deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne is rushing towards his century! Short delivery bowled outside off, Marnus Labuschagne opens the face of the bat to guide it to the right of gully towards the deep backward point boundary!
Outside off and slightly back of a length. Marnus Labuschagne fends this towards gully.
Kasun Rajitha goes back to bowling full at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Full delivery with some gentle shape away from outside off, Marnus Labuschagne fends this towards cover.
On a good length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne works this to the left of backward point but is not able to take a single.
Flatter and a little bit of turn into the batter, Smith defends off the back foot.
Tosses it up on middle, Smith works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Full toss and put away! This is on off, Smith hits it down the ground and bags a boundary. Smith is not going to miss out on that. He has his eye in and now moves into the 40s.
On middle, Smith hangs back and works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, blocked.
Angled into the pads, Smith works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
NO BALL! Kasun Rajitha serves this on a good length outside off, Steven Smith does a little shimmy before leaving the ball. The umpire calls no ball and the ball has to be bowled again.
Closer to the stumps but still wideenough from a good length for Steven Smith not to play at it.
On a good length outside off. Steven Smith fends this off towards backward point.
Kasun Rajitha goes full now outside off, Steven Smith comes across the stumps and defends it down the pitch.
On a good length with some shape in. Steven Smith fends this off casually towards cover.
Wide from off stump and full, Steven Smith goes towards the ball and hits it to deep cover for a single.
Good shape away from outside off, bowled on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller delivery angled into the pads, Steven Smith plays this past short leg towards square leg.

FOUR! Juicy full toss that got what it deserved! Ramesh Mendis flights the ball and does not get it to pitch, Steven Smith is in good form as he does not miss out and works it through covers for a boundary. One run away from his half century!

That is 50 for Steven Smith! Ramesh Mendis goes 'round the wicket. The field is set for the leg side but he delivers this short and outside off, Steven Smith gives a solid punch through covers to get to another Test fifty!
Full and angled into the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne gets his front foot forward and defends solidly.
Marnus Labuschagne uses his feet to a full delivery outside off and plays it to the left of cover for a single.
Short and angled down leg, Steven Smith plays this easily fine of the backward square leg fielder to retain strike with a single.
Good length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Well outside off, left alone.
Another one well wide outside off, not played at.
Really don't think this will frustrate Smith! He would leave it all day. Another one outside off, not played at.
Another one on a length and around off, Smith gets right behind the line and defends.
That is a beauty! This lands on a length and around off, it lands and then moves away. Smith looks to push at it, it goes off the outside edge but lands well short of first slip.

Prabath Jayasuriya begins with a flighted delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne welcomes him with a charge down the pitch to connect the full toss and dispatch it through covers for a boundary. Gets to 99 and a run away from a very good century!
Back-of-a-length delivery in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne comes ahead and pushes it towards mid on.

That is 100 for Marnus Labuschagne! His first outside of Australia and boy, he really needed this knock! This will give him immense confidence and give him the belief that he can score runs anywhere. He was given a chance earlier and has made most of it. A very elegant knock by him and he has scored at a brisk rate too. He would love to make this into a big ton now. Gets there by working it towards mid-wicket and takes one. All his teammates are on their feet, applauding the effort.
Prabath Jayasuriya tempts Steven Smith with a full delivery outside off, Steven Smith hits this straight towards the cover fielder.
Full on off stump, Steven Smith defends this towards cover.
Full once again outside off, Steven Smith takes a larger stride and defends this to covers as well.
Goes slightly full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it well.
Good-length delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne drives on the up and can not pierce the field as he finds extra cover.
Short delivery outside off, Marnus Labuschagne stays on the back foot and defends it towards cover.
Short and wide outside off, Marnus Labuschagne feels it is too wide for him to play at.
Outside off stump line on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne uses his wrists to work this between mid on and mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Angling down leg and full, Marnus Labuschagne works this through square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off, Smith strokes it to mid off.
Another run! On middle, this is worked to mid on for a single.
On off, defended.

OUT! STUMPED! Sri Lanka strike at the stroke of Tea! FIRST TEST WICKET FOR Prabath Jayasuriya! A big moment for him and it is a wicket he will not forget, he gets the better of Marnus Labuschagne! That though spun a long way. Marnus Labuschagne can't believe what just happened. He looks to use his feet again, this time however, Prabath Jayasuriya drags his length back a little. Marnus Labuschagne tries to defend but the ball turns away ever so sharply and Dickwella does not make a mistake this time. He throws the ball in anger onto the ground after removing the bails off. End of an outstanding innings from him. He walks back along with the other as it is TEA ON DAY 1!
Howout: st Niroshan Dickwella b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Full delivery to start proceedings, outside off. Travis Head defends awkwardly towards point.
Full and angling into the stumps, Travis Head goes back and knocks it towards mid on.
Flighted full on middle, Steven Smith taps this down towards short leg.
Full once again on off, Steven Smith defends this towards short mid on.

Way too short from Ramesh Mendis angled into the pads, Steven Smith pulls this towards the backward square leg boundary where a good from Dinesh Chandimal prevents four runs! Still get two runs though.
Straight delivery angled into the pads, Steven Smith plays for the turn early and gets beaten.
Straying down leg, and goes off Steven Smith's thigh pad fine for a couple of leg byes.
Full and on the pads, tapped down to short leg.
Full and angled into the left-hander, as he sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and on the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket and more misfield as Steven Smith goes across for a single.
Shorter outside off, Travis Head fends it off his backfoot for towards mid on.
Full and outside off, keeps its line. Travis Head cuts this to deep point for a single.
Back-of-a-length delivery spinning towards the leg, Steven Smith tucks this through square leg for a single.
Full and in line with the stumps, Travis Head flicks this towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Finds the gap with ease! Full and outside off, a half volley, this is driven through covers.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Fatter and on off, defended.
On off, quicker, kept out.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On the stumps, defended.
Flighted full outside off, Steven Smith fends this towards point.
Full once again on a middle stump line. Steven Smith defends this back to the bowler.
Full and on leg, Steven Smith stays back and taps it down to his feet.
Outside off stump now and full. Steven Smith solidly behind this one as he plays it towards cover.
Angling in from outside off and full, Steven Smith plays this down the wicket.
Full and angled in once more. Steven Smith plays out a rare maiden over!
Short and coming in from outside off, Steven Smith plays this off the back foot for a single to deep cover.
Turning in from outside off and slightly short, Steven Smith turns this towards short fine leg for a single.
Short and wide from off stump, Travis Head uses the depth of the crease and works this through covers for a single.
Big turn once again as this pitches outside off and goes down leg, Well stopped by the fielder at leg gully.
Short and coming in from outside off, Steven Smith plays this off the back foot for a single to deep point.
Flighted full and on off, Travis Head comes forward and defends firmly.
Flatter and on off, it is played back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, Smith guides it through point for one.
He had to get bat on that! On middle, Head goes down on one knee and looks to sweep, it goes off the underedge down to fine leg for one.
Tosses it up nicely, it dips as it nears the batter. Blocked.
Well bowled again! Floats it up on off, gets it to drift back in. Defended.
Three really good balls to end! Another one on the stumps, kept out.
Full and turning away from the left-hander. Travis Head manages to knock this down towards short cover.
Outside off and goes full, Travis Head works this toward mid off and gets off strike.
Goes full and turning into the stumps, Steven Smith gets an inside edge towards leg gully.
Full outside off, gets some turn, and gets an inside edge onto the pads that almost rolls onto the stumps.
In line with the stumps and delivered full, Steven Smith defends this back down the pitch.
Short and angled into the pads, Steven Smith works it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Half an appeal but that is never going to be out! Smith comes down the track, the length is shortened and it is the arm ball. Smith looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, defended.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
Loopy ball on off, Smith keeps it out nicely.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the stumps, this is pushed to covers.
Back-of-a-length and turning in from outside off, Steven Smith plays this back to the bowler.
Short once again and angling into the pads, Steven Smith works this towards deep square leg for a single.
Goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander. Angles this in from a shorter length and Travis Head defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted full outside off, Travis Head tries to work it offside but mistimes it back to Ramesh Mendis.
Fuller and angled into the stumps, Travis Head goes back and fends it off.
Short and coming into the batter, Travis Head makes room and plays it to the left of cover and collects two runs.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On off, blocked.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
A single as this is pushed down to long on.
On off, kept out.
Two more! Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
Full and angling in from outside off, Grips of the surface and Travis Head is well forward to defend.
Full and angled into the stumps, Travis Head knocks this back to the bowler.
Quicker delivery around off, Travis Head fends this off solidly.
Flighted full and on off stump, Travis Head taps this to off side.
turns outside off and is not short enough for Travis Head to cut as he gets beaten.
Tossed up full on off, Travis Head defends and now Maheesh Theekshana gets his first maiden over!
On middle, kept out.
Steps out and drives it nicely to mid on.
On the stumps, defended.
Slower through the air and on the pads, kept out.
Slows it up and bowls it outside off, Smith looks to push it on the off side but it goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
Flighted and on off, defended.
Full and pitching on leg, Travis Head works this towards mid-wicket.
Full outside off, Travis Head works this toward mid off and wants to get off strike. Just about makes it and the throw from the fielder is wild.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, pushed towards the vacant cover region for a single.
Full outside off, Travis Head works it towards cover for a single.
Shorter delivery onto the pads, Steven Smith plays this to the right of mid-wicket for a single.
Full and angled into the pads, Travis Head shifts his weight back and works it towards point for a single.
On off, kept out.

OUT! TIMBER! Prabath Jayasuriya has another! Head was reluctant to walk back but after the replays, he has to. He just played down the wrong line here. This is tossed up, it starts on middle but then drifts away a touch. Head plays inside the line, probably for the turn. Wrong idea as there is not a lot of turn on this surface. It lands goes on with the arm and clips the off pole. Head waits as he feels it is Dickwella who knocks the bails off. The umpires take it upstairs and replays show that Head has to walk back. Replays also showed that Head put in a small stride forward, had he taken a big stride, he may have put bat to ball.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
Steps out and then pushes this ball to the man at covers.
On middle, Smith defends it back to the bowler.
Serves this quicker, fuller, around middle. Cameron Green pushes it towards cover.
Spinning in, full again, around off. Cameron Green advances down the track and blocks it out.
Tad quicker, a little bit of drift on that one, around middle and leg. Cameron Green blocks it out solidly.
Pitches it up, around middle. Cameron Green defends it out watchfully.
Serves this one very full, outside off. Cameron Green steps down and yorks himself. He fails to dig this one out, Niroshan Dickwella fails to collect the ball as well. A missed stumping chance!
This one lands around the leg pole, and spins away a tad, around middle. Cameron Green defends this one. A maiden from Maheesh Theekshana!
On the stumps, kept out.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the stumps, it is defended.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Whipped away! Steps out and gets to the pitch of it, it is worked wide of the mid on fielder for a boundary.
On off, blocked.
Shorter, around off. Cameron Green pushes this one off the back foot towards cover.
Tosses this one up, full in length, around off. Cameron Green dances down the pitch and drives it towards mid off for a quick single.
Quicker, fuller, and on middle. Steven Smith defends it out solidly.
Pitches it up again, around middle. Steven Smith lunges forward and blocks it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Steven Smith is not going to miss out on these! Very full on this occasion, outside off, slower through the air as well. Steven Smith drives it past point for a boundary.
Tad shorter, spinning in around middle and off. Steven Smith blocks this one.
On middle, Green lunges and keeps it out.
Green steps out and pushes this to mid off for one.
That is a beauty! It is tossed up, it drifts in, lands and then spins away. Smith is beaten as he tries to block.
On middle, kept out.
On the off pole, it pushed towards cover for one.

A HUGE APPEAL AND THE FINGER IS RAISED! Green revews but it seems out! OUT! The impact was umpire's call and hence, Australia do not lose a review but they are 5 down all of a sudden and Prabath Jayasuriya has another wicket. This is flatter and around off, Green walks across and looks to sweep but misses to get hit on the pads. A huge appeal and the finger is raised. Green reviews but in vain. Sri Lanka crawling back into the game now.
Outside off, fuller ball. Steven Smith lunges forward and blocks it towards point.
Pitches it up again, quicker at 90 clicks, on middle. Steven Smith shows the full face of the bat and blocks it out.
Spinning in, around middle, full in length. Steven Smith prods forward and knocks it towards long on for a single.

A huge shout for an LBW, but the umpire says no! Maheesh Theekshana goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and serves a fuller ball, around middle. Alex Carey gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses. Sri Lanka skipper does opt for a review but it's a little late. The replay though shows that Alex Carey had got a little glove on that one.
Outside off, fuller one. Alex Carey blocks it out off the front foot.
Tad shorter, outside off. Alex Carey cuts it towards backward point and takes a single. He retains the strike!
The reverse sweep is out, it is hit through point for one.
On off, defended.
Flatter and on middle, Smith keeps it out.
Another one on the stumps, blocked.
Floats it up on off, defended.
A single to end as this is pushed through covers.
FOUR! That is easily done! What good timing from Steven Smith! Maheesh Theekshana floats this full outside off, Steven Smith works this through cover for an elegant boundary!
Serves this full and angling into the stumps, Steven Smith defends this back to the bowler.
Shorter in length and angling down leg, Steven Smith turns this towards fine leg for a single.
'Round the wicket to the left-hander, angling in from outside off, Alex Carey pushes forward and plays it back to the bowler.
Full and pitching on leg stump, Alex Carey tries to work this leg side and gets a leading edge towards cover.
Maheesh Theekshana fires this quicker outside off stump. Alex Carey knocks this towards cover.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
On the stumps again, blocked.
On the stumps, defended.
A quick run! On off, this is pushed to mid off. The batters go for one and complete it.
FOUR! He is just so good at these shots! On middle, fuller, Carey plays the reverse sweep, it goes through point for a boundary.
Angled into the pads, Carey works it to mid-wicket.
Full toss going down leg side, Steven Smith will be really disappointed he did not put that away. Hits him on his pads and Niroshan Dickwella is the only one appealing.
Down leg side once again and slightly short, Steven Smith works this off his body towards backward square leg for a single.
Fraction short and outside off, Alex Carey cuts this straight to point.
Maheesh Theekshana continues to bowl short outside off, Alex Carey is not able to find the gap as he cuts this straight to backward point.
Maheesh Theekshana bowls this full and slightly wide, Alex Carey gets deceived by the slower delivery and mistimes it through covers for a single.

FOUR! Maheesh Theekshana ​​​​​​feeds Steven Smith with a really loose delivery! Short and angling down leg side, Steven Smith goes back and pulls this past backward square leg for an easy boundary! He is now one big hit away from reaching yet another century!
On the stumps, blocked.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, Smith defends.
Flighted ball and on off, this is kept out.
Fires it on off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.

Kasun Rajitha begins by delivering a full delivery going down leg, Alex Carey gets pad to it and works it leg side. There is some misunderstanding and Steven Smith sends him back but an overthrow finally allows them to pick up a single leg bye.
On a good length outside off, Steven Smith guides this through the vacant point region for an easy single.
Kasun Rajitha serves this full outside off, Alex Carey fends this back to the bowler.
Full and angling into the pads once again. Alex Carey gets it off his pads to square leg and takes a single. Leg bye is given by the umpire.

FOUR! GETS TO HIS TON IN STYLE! Smith has a relieved look on his face after getting to the milestone and understandably he has scored one after quite some time. He gets a half volley outside which he thrashes through the off side. There were two fielders in the cover region and he gets past both of them and into the fence. A very hard-working innings. Can he make it into a big one now?
On off, defended.
Full and angling towards the leg stump, Alex Carey works this towards short mid on.
Onto the pads once more, Alex Carey nudges this past square leg for a single.
Goes around the wicket to the right-hander and gets it full into the stumps, Steven Smith takes a couple of strides forward and plays it back to the bowler.
Fraction shorter this time on off, Steven Smith goes on the back foot and plays it to the cover fielder.
Full delivery into the pads, Steven Smith taps it down to the left of short leg.
Prabath Jayasuriya fires this straight into the pads, Steven Smith is solidly behind this one as he now plays for Stumps.
Shorter and on the body, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.

FOUR! Steven Smith is not missing out on his gifts though! Kasun Rajitha delivers this short and wide from off stump. Steven Smith is seeing the ball really well and smashes it through covers for a boundary!
Kasun Rajitha goes full and outside off, Steven Smith gets a bottom edge towards mid on.
Full delivery wide outside off, Steven Smith hits this hard towards cover.
Hint of late swing as this is delivered full and outside off, Steven Smith does not bother playing at it.
Goes even fuller this time but still outside off and Steven Smith is aware that he does not have to play at these.
On off, defended.
Flatter and on off, kept out.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
On off, blocked.
FOUR! That is creamed! A full toss on off, this is driven through covers for a boundary.
On middle, defended.
Kasun Rajitha bangs this in short and angles it down leg, Steven Smith pulls this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Serves this full and wide outside off stump, Alex Carey is watchful as he lets this one through to the keeper.
That is a really good delivery from Kasun Rajitha, Angles it in from 'round the wicket and gets the ball to nip back in from a good length. Alex Carey manages to get an inside edge onto his pads.
Low full toss outside off stump, Alex Carey does not make use of it and mistimes it towards cover for a single.
WIDE! Banged in short into Steven Smith once again. But this one is really high and is called wide.
Good-length delivery outside off, Steven Smith works this towards cover-point.
Really full, almost yorker length and outside off, Steven Smith looks to play this offside but gets an inside edge towards backward square leg for a single.
Full and delivered on off stump. Steven Smith fends this back to the bowler.
Spinning into the pads from outside off, Steven Smith works this to square leg for a single.

Full and on middle, turn away from the batter as he fends it towards backward point. Steven Smith wants to get back on strike and rushes Alex Carey for a single. He would have been short had it been a direct hit.
Full delivery outside off, Steven Smith gets a long stride forward and smothers the ball into the pitch.
Short delivery in line with the stumps, Steven Smith goes back in the crease and punches it towards long on for a single.
Fired into the pads on a full length, Alex Carey taps it down towards silly point.
Flighted full into middle, Steven Smith guides this towards mid on.
Prabath Jayasuriya strays down leg from a shorter length, Steven Smith guides this easily towards square leg for a single.
Off stump line and slightly short, Alex Carey defends this back down the pitch.
Angled into the pads from outside off, Alex Carey works this towards mid-wicket.
Prabath Jayasuriya serves this full on the pads, Alex Carey can not get this away as it rolls towards leg gully.
Quicker delivery attacking the stumps, Alex Carey uses his wrists and flicks it towards mid-wicket. The umpire checks his watch and says 'that's it boys' to call Stumps on DAY 1.
Tossed up, around off. Smith prods and defends it.

Smith survives! Sharp spin already here! Tossed up, full and outside off, spins in sharply. Smith tries to defend with bat and pad together but misses and gets hit on the pads. A massive appeal for LBW but nothing given! Mendis convinces the skipper to review it and Sri Lanka take the review. Ultra Edge confirms no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows impact is outside off. Review lost!
Floated ball, around off. Smith skips down and eases it to long on for a single.
Angles a full ball, on leg. Carey pushes it to mid on.
A quicker one, length and on middle. Carey gets inside the line and blocks it.
On middle, blocked out.
Length ball, sliding down the leg side. Smith looks to flick but misses.
TAP AND RUN! A length ball, around off and nips back in. Smith prods and drops it in front of covers and takes off for a quick single. Good running there.
On a length and on middle. Carey solidly blocks it.
A full ball, drifting down the leg side. Carey looks to whip away but misses and gets hit on the pads.
A fuller ball, outside off, slanting in. Carey looks for a big booming drive but misses.
Again comes in with the angle but Carey stays back and drives it straight to mid off.
Shorter and outside off. Smith punches off the back foot, wide of long off for a couple of runs. 50-run stand between these two.
A flighted ball, outside off. Smith leans and blocks it.
Sliding on the pads. Smith tickles it to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up on the pads. Carey tucks it to square leg for an easy single.
FOUR! First boundary of the Day! Tossed up, around leg. Smith gets on his knee and tries to sweep but top edges it in the vacant deep square leg region for a boundary.
Shorter and on leg. Smith clears his front leg and nudges it past short leg for a single. 9 runs off the over.
A length ball, outside off. Smith shoulders arms to it.
Too full and on middle. Smith drives it nicely but straight to mid on.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Smith flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Way outside off, easy leave.
Short of a length and just outside off. Smith gets on his toes and punches it to covers for a single.
Drops a short ball and on middle. Carey pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full, quicker and on middle. Carey gets on the front foot to block it.
Jayasuriya targets the stumps. Carey blocks it again.
Floated, around middle and leg. Alex tucks it to square leg.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! He loves to play this kind of shot! Tossed up, around off. Carey reverse sweeps it through point and wide of the fielder in the deep as well.
Again reverse sweeps this full ball to point for a single.

FOUR! Australia are scoring runs at a quick rate! Another boundary and this time from the blade of the centurion! Flighted, full and outside off. Smith comes down the track and smashes it through mid on for a boundary.
Full and outside off. Carey blocks it to covers.
Length and on off. Defended back to the bowler.
This is full and outside off. Carey tries to play the cover drive but mistimes it back to the bowler.
Touch fuller and outside off. Carey punches it to covers.
Length and angling on top of off. Carey bunts it on the leg side.
FOUR! Wonderful stroke! Overpitched, outside off. Carey stays back and drives it through covers, through the gap for four.
Tossed up on middle. Defended on the front foot.
Angles a full ball on off. Smith lunges and blocks it solidly.
Slightly slower, full and on off. Another solid block from Steven.
Tossed up, outside off. Smith looks to defend but outer edges it to short third man. Carey wants a single but Smith is not interested in it.
Tad short and on middle. Smith rocks back and turns it to square leg.
Full and on off. Smith prods and defends it out.
A length ball, around off at 131 kph. Carey hangs back and defends with strong hands.
Slight width there, outside off, it is driven straight to the man at covers.
Almost pinged on the pads! Good pace from Rajitha! A length ball on middle. Carey is a bit rushed as he flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, way outside off. Smith works it to sweeper cover for a single.
Too full and wide of off. Carey hits it to covers.
Fuller and around off. Carey on drives it but straight to mid on.
Flatter and on middle. Smith wrists it to square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Sri Lanka finally break the 77-run stand and get rid of Carey! Prabath Jayasuriya gets his fourth wicket here! Tossed up full and outside off. Alex Carey who was playing the reverse sweep so well till now tries again but the ball bounces and takes the top edge. It goes in the air and to covers where Ramesh Mendis was stationed. Sri Lanka will look to take the remaining wickets quickly now.
Howout: c Ramesh Mendis b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Shorter and around middle and leg. Starc stays back and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but not given.
On the pads again, flicked to square leg and Starc gets off the mark with a single.
Too full and on middle, driven to long off for a single.
On off, kept out.
Length ball on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Smith pushes it to deep covers for a single.
Fuller and on middle. Strac drives it straight but the bowler gets a hand to it. No run.
On a length and slanting on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
This one drifts on middle. Starc keeps it out.
Way outside off, fuller. Left alone.
Oh, this was close. Tossed up on off, Steven Smith looks to sweep it but misses as the ball hits his thigh. A loud appeal but the finger stays down.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Prabath Jayasuriya picks up his fifth wicket of the game. Tossed up outside off, Mitchell Starc looks to push it towards the off side but gets a thick outside edge and goes towards first slip where Kusal Mendis takes a sharp catch to his right. The debutant gets a five-fer!
Howout: c Kusal Mendis b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Tossed up outside off, this is defended well.

FOUR! Outside off again, Pat Cummins looks to play at it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races towards third man. Kusal Mendis makes a good stop before the fence as he slides but it rebounds through the toe of the other fielder standing near him and clears the fence.
Keeps bowling it outside off, Pat Cummins drives it towards long off for one.
Tossed up on off, Steven Smith looks to sweep at it but misses and hits his thigh. A slight appeal but the umpire is uninterested.
Oh, this was close. Lands it just outside off, Pat Cummins looks to defend it but misses. The ball just aired past his bat and the off pole.
Bowls it on off, Pat Cummins defends it away.

OUT! LBW! This one lands on off, on a length. Pat Cummins looks to block it but misses and the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down. Sri Lanka go for a review. No bat there. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Pat Cummins has to walk away. A good start for Sri Lanka so far in this session. Can they bag the Aussies before the session ends?
Goes fuller and on off, this is played towards the mid on fielder.
Bowls it outside off, Nathan Lyon cuts it towards point for one.
fuller and down the leg side, Steven Smith works it towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Tossed up on off, Steven Smith plays it towards the off side for one.
FOUR! This is well connected. Bowls it fuller and on off, Nathan Lyon sweeps it through deep square leg for a boundary.
This was similar to the last delivery, Nathan Lyon sweeps again but finds the fielder at square leg.
This one drifts a bit, Nathan Lyon looks to sweep it but misses.

OUT! LBW! Tossed up on leg, Nathan Lyon hangs back looks to flick it but misses. A loud appeal for LBW but not given. The umpire takes a while but raises his finger in the end. Nathan Lyon takes a review immediately. No bat involved. Ball Tracking takes a while to load but shows three reds. Nathan Lyon had walked out already when he saw the replay as he knew the outcome. Sri Lanka need one more wicket now!
Tossed-up delivery, Mitchell Swepson defends it well.
Tossed up on leg, Steven Smith looks to play at it but couldn't connect well.
On off, defended out.
Goes fuller again, Steven Smith eases it towards the leg side and rotates the strike.
Tossed up on middle and drifting into the batter, Mitchell Swepson defends it away.
Tossed up on middle, Mitchell Swepson works it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
On off, this is defended towards the leg side.
FOUR BYES! Bowls it outside leg, Steven Smith looks to flick it but missees. The keeper misses it as well as the ball races the fine leg fence. 350 up for the Aussies.
On off, defended out.
Fuller and on middle, Steven Smith scoops it towards fine leg. The fielder chases it well. Three runs taken.
Bowls it on off, Mitchell Swepson defends it back towards Prabath Jayasuriya.
Goes outside off, Mitchell Swepson defends it awkwardly towards the off side.
On middle, Mitchell Swepson eases it towards short mid-wicket fielder.
Floated on off, Smith blocks it out.
Slower through the air, driftin in, Smith tries to play at it but could not connect.
Floated on the middle, Smith looks for flick but gets hit on his pads.
Tossed up around leg, Smith lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on leg, Smith works it through square leg for one.
Flighted delivery on off, Mitchell Swepson blocks it out.
short and outside off, Smith guides to third man but denies for the single.
Full on off, Smith drives it long off. No run there too.
A bit short outside off, Smith dabs it to third man.
Turn and Bounce. This is tossed up on middle, turning away a bit. Smith tries to play at it but gets beaten.
Floated on off, Smith makes room and plays over extra cover for a run.
On off, blocked well.
Full and on off, Smith drives it through covers for a run.
Tossed up on off, Swepson goes for the drive but it gets an outside edge and goes towards third man. They run three.
A bit short on middle and leg, Smith clips it long on.
On a length on middle, drifting on. Smith flicks this off his back foot to the leg side for one.
Floated on middle, Swepson defends it well.
Tossed up on the pads, Swepson glances it to leg slip.
Tossed up outside off, turning away. Smith leaves it alone.
Floated around leg, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket but refuses for the single.
Tossed up on the middle, Smith comes down the pitch and guides it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Tossed up around off, Smith leans on to play at it but it just goes past his outside edge.
Short and on middle, Smith punches it of his back foot to long on. He takes the single this time.
Darted this onto the pads, Swepson defends it out.
Starts on a length outside off, Smith punches it to point.
Floated on the off, Smith pushes it to covers.
Tossed up on off, turning away. Smith steers it from his back foot towards point.
Full and on the pads, Smith clips it wide of mid on. He calls for two and gets two.
Slower through the air on off, Smith drives it well through covers for a single.

OUT! LBW! Australia's innings come to an end at 364. Slightly shorter and on middle, Mitchell Swepson looks to play at it but misses and the finger goes up immidiately. It is plumb dead in front but Australia go for a review. No bat involved. Ball Tracking shows three reds.
Starts with a fuller one outside off, Pathum Nissanka drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Another fuller angling into the batter, Pathum Nissanka defends it well.
An inswinger on middle, Pathum Nissanka looks to block it but gets a thick inside edge and rolls towards square leg. They take a single.
Goes outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it towards covers for one.
Outside off again, Pathum Nissanka guides it towards the vacant silly point region and scampers for a quick single.
Fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
On a length and on off, Pathum Nissanka defends it towards the off side.
On middle this time, Pathum Nissanka defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Nissanka looks to play at it but misses.
Flicks a fuller ball towards backward square leg for one.
Half volley down the leg side, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Pathum Nissanka defends it back towards the bowler.
Lands it on a full length and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne nudges it towards short mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
On off, defended out.
On a length and on off, Pathum Nissanka eases it towards silly mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Goes outside off again, Pathum Nissanka looks to play at it but misses.
Another one outside off, Pathum Nissanka lets it through and towards the keeper. That will be Lunch on Day 2.
Starts with a fuller one on off, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it back towards the bowler again.
This one lands fuller and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
On middle this time, Dimuth Karunaratne plays it straight. The ball hits the stumps at the non-striker's end and rolls towards the fielder at mid off.
Goes outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Outside off again, Dimuth Karunaratne lets it go towards the keeper.
Goes fuller and outside off, Pathum Nissanka eases it towards the off side.
On a length and on leg, Pathum Nissanka flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a single.
Fuller one on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne nudges it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Another fuller delivery, Dimuth Karunaratne plays it towards the mid off fielder.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it solidly off the front foot.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne waits for the ball and plays a late cut shot towards backward point. They take a single.
Touch fuller delivery, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it well.
Another fuller one, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it solidly.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to play at it but gets a thick inside edge and the ball hits his pads and rolls away.
Shorter one and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it.
Shorter one again, this time down the leg side. Dimuth Karunaratne ducks underneath it again.
Touch fuller this time, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it towards the off side.
This one lands fuller and on leg, Pathum Nissanka flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace. This is good running between the wickets.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller one outside off, Pathum Nissanka drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
On a length and on middle, Pathum Nissanka awkwardly flicks it towards mid on fielder.
Outside off this time, Pathum Nissanka plays it towards point.
Bowls it fuller and outside off again, Pathum Nissanka drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
On a length outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to short mid off.
Full and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne moves across and drives it mid on.
Good length on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it to the leg side.
Bangs it short this time on middle and leg, Dimuth Karunaratne ducks underneath it.
On a lengtth outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne punches this one straight to mid off.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to pull it over the square leg but could not connect well.
Full and outside off, Pathum Nissanka blocks it back to the bowler.
Full again outside off,angling away. Pathum Nissanka lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Mitchell Starc delivers it back of length, outside off, moving away. Pathum Nissanka reaches out for it without any footwork, it takes the outside edge and flies towards gully where Cameron Green takes a blinder of a catch as he dives to his left. A stunning catch and Australia break the opening stand.
Howout: c Cameron Green b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Full and on middle, Kusal Mendis defends it solidly off his front foot.
Fuller and outside off, angling away. Kusal Mendis offers no shot.
On a length outside off, Kusal Mendis leaves it alone.
Floated around middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on off, Kusal Mendis defends it of his back foot.
Floated outside off, Kusal Mendis defends it well.
Lyon is not giving anything away. Floated on off again, Kusal Mendis plays a back foot defense.
Slower through the air on off, Kusal Mendis blocks it to the off side.
Full and outside off, Kusal Mendis leans on and drives it through covers for a single.
Fuller and outside off, slanting it away. Mendis shoulders arms to this one.
Good length and on off, defended.
That is a good leave! Another one on a length and just outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, Mendis hangs back and defends.
Really good carry for Starc! We have seen good bounce on this wicket. Length and outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
A maiden then by Starc! On off again, consistent lines and lengths from him. Mendis negotiates it well.
Looks to toss it up but bowls it a little too full, this is pushed to covers.
Catch it is the cry but it lands short! Shorter and around off, extra bounce on this one. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to cut but it goes off the top edge and on the bounce to point.
Floats it up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to covers.
A quick run! Flatter and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards mid on for one.
Pushes this one through and lands it on off, it is pushed to mid on.
Very nicely bowled! Loopy delivery, gets it to drift away and then turn back in a little from off. Defended.
On off, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it out.
On the stumps, it is kept out well.
That is a nasty delivery! Short and on the body, this one takes off after landing! Karunaratne fends it away awkwardly. Luckily for him, it lands safe on the off side.
Two! Shorter and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne rides on top of the bounce nicely and then plays it through point for two.
Good length and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne plays it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side, Dimuth Karunaratne hangs back and defends.
Flatter and on off, Mendis hangs back and keeps it out.

That was very close! Slows it up, lands it outside off and gets it to turn back in a little. Mendis leaves, it just about shaves the off pole. There was an explosion too when the ball pitched. Lyon won't mind that.
Another one tossed up on off, this turns back in. Mendis works it to mid-wicket.
Quicker and on off, Mendis defends.
Shorter and on off, Mendis pushes it towards cover for one.
Floats it up on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it to mid on.
Length again and outside off, Mendis shoulders arms to this one.
Yet another delivery outside off, Mendis does not fiddle with it.
FOUR! That is played brilliantly! Shorter and on off, Mendis hangs back and guides it through point. This one races away to the fence in no time.
That is a beauty! It had everything but the edge! Length and on off, it is angled into the batter. Mendis looks to defend but it lands and moves away. Mendis is beaten.
On middle, Mendis works it to mid on.
Relentless stuff from Cummins! Solidly played though from Mendis! Good length and on off, kept out.
FOUR! That is beautifully timed! Steps out and gets to the pitch of it, he just pushes it through mid on and this one races away to the fence.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Just outside off, left alone.
On the stumps, blocked.
Fuller and on middle, Karunaratne works it to mid on.
FOUR! Easy pickings and that is the second boundary of the over! On the pads, fuller, this is clipped through mid-wicket, no one in that region and it races away to the fence.
Outside off, on a length, Mendis covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
Outside off, Mendis shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, not played at.
Angled into the pads, this is clipped through square leg for one.
On the stumps, defended.
Floated around middle and leg, Mendis blocks it to short leg.

FOUR! Poor Fielding. This is a bit short and outside off, Mendis goes on his back foot and cuts it to point where Mitchell Starc puts in the dive early but could not stop it and it goes for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Mendis pushes it to long off for a run.
