Floated on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it of his front foot.
Full and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it to square leg.
Arm ball onto the stumps, Karunaratne comes forward to play at it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.

Dimuth Karunaratne was a goner! He had given up there! On middle, this is worked to mid on and Dimuth Karunaratne takes off. He is sent back from halfway. The fielder picks the ball, Starc and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The fielder from cover who was running in, collects the ball and then he tries to underarm it onto the stumps as Karunaratne was slow in coming back. He misses too. Lucky escape.
On off, defended.
A bumper, it is ducked under.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Yet another delivery outside off, Mendis does not fiddle with it.
A dot to end! Outside off, Mendis points his bat skywards and leaves it alone.
Half an appeal but turned down! Dimuth Karunaratne steps out, the length is shortened. He looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads.
On off, fuller, this is pushed to mid off.
Flatter and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it towards cover for one.
Angled into the pads, Mendis works it towards fine leg for one.
Shorter and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne hangs back and keeps it out.
FOUR! That is creamed! Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne comes down the track and strokes it past mid off for a boundary.
Good length on off, angling in. Kusal Mendis knocks it to mid on.
Full and outside off, shaping in. Kusal Mendis lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
On a length and on off, Mendis leans forward and plays a solid defense to silly mid off.
Good length on off, Kusal Mendis blocks it to the off side.
Good length on off, holds its line. Mendis offers no shot.
FOUR! Beautiful Shot. This lands a bit short on middle and leg, Mendis pulls it towards the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, blocked off well.
Flatter and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne moves forward and drives it straight to mid on.
Tossed up on off, defended back towards the bowler.
Floated on off, pushed towards point.
Slower through the air on off, turning away. Dimuth Karunaratne comes down the pitch and tries to flick it to mid-wicket but gets a leading edge and the balls falls short of the extra cover fielder.
Full and on off, driven to short extra cover.
On a length outside off, Mendis blocks it to the off side.
A bit fuller onto the stumps, Mendis defends it down the pitch.
Bangs it short on middle, Mendis ducks underneath it. Its called a wide for height.
On a length and on middle, Mendis blocks it well again.
Back of length outside off, Mendis pushes this towards gully.
Pulls his length back again outside off, Kusal Mendis gets on top of the bounce and guides it through point for a single.
Full and down the leg side, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards deep square leg for a run.
Loopy delivery on off, turning away. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to defend it but the bounce takes the top edge and it goes to short third man.
Floated on off, defended well.
Slower through the air on off, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it to short covers.
FOUR! Easy pickings. This is short and wide outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne goes on his back foot and cuts it past the point for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne uses his feet and defends.
Short and wide, Dimuth Karunaratne offers no shot.
Back of a length, Kusal Mendis knocks it to covers.
Full and angling in, Kusal Mendis flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full-toss onto the stumps, Dimuth Karunaratne drives it straight to the bowler.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Back of a length outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne reaches out for it and gets an outside edge but luckily for him it did not carry to the first slip.
Full and angling onto the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it to the on side.
Lands it short and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Tossed up on off. Karunaratne prods and blocks it out.
Slightly short and around off. Karunaratne rocks back and cuts it to point.
Shorter again. Karunaratne punches this time off the back foot to covers.
Bowls it on the pads. Karunaratne lets it through without offering a shot.
On the pads, this time Karunaratne tucks it to square leg for a single.
Fuller and outside off. Mendis lunges and blocks it out.
Serves it on a length and wide outside off. Dimuth leaves it alone.
Angles a length ball, outside off. Karunaratne gets on the front foot to defend but gets a thick outside edge to point.
Length and outside off. Blocked to covers.
Two runs! This one drifts in, fuller and on off. Karunaratne turns it to mid-wicket and calls for two. Mendis makes his ground before the throw comes in.
Shorter and on middle. Karunaratne sits under it.
Full and on middle, tucked to the left of mid-wicket for one more.
A flighted full ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Too full and around off. Karunaratne skips down and drills it to long on for one.
Good run! Tossed up, just outside off. Mendis drops it to point for a single.
Shorter, quicker and on middle. Kept out.
A juicy full toss, outside off. Karunaratne smashes but straight back to Swepson.
Fuller and around middle. Karunaratne nudges it to mid-wicket. 2 runs off Swepson's first over.
A flatter ball, around off. Mendis hangs back to defend.
Tries to serve on the rough but this is outside off. Mendis slaps it through covers for a brace. The 50-run stand is up.
Full and on off. Defended out.
Full, slanting on off, quicker too. Mendis blocks it on the back foot.
On middle, blocked out.
Quicker, shorter and on off. Mendis thinks of the pull shot first but fends it away to mid-wicket.
This one spins back in sharply from off. Karunaratne stays back and punches it to covers.
Tossed up on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.

Dropped! Should have been taken! A full toss on middle. Karunaratne pushes it straight back to Swepson who did not anticipate it to come back and his follow-through was taking him to the leg side, so it made more hard for him. He gets a right-hand to it but fails to stop. The ball lobs behind him for a single.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off. Mendis works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted ball, full and on off. Karunaratne drives it to mid off. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Floated ball on off. Mendis uses his feet as he drills it to long on for one.
Very full and on leg. Karunaratne bunts it straight to mid-wicket.
Slower one, around off. Karunaratne punches it to point where the fielder runs back and to his left but fails to stop. Two taken.
On off, defended out.
Fuller, around off. Karunaratne leans and dead bats it.
A loopy ball on middle. Karunaratne eases it to mid on.
FOUR! Beats the fielder! Pitches it up, outside off. Mendis drives it firmly to mid off where it beats Khawaja to his right and races to the fence.
Length and on middle. Blocked out.
Bowls one on the hips. Mendis tucks it straight to square leg.
Starc keeps bowling on the leg side, this time on the pads. Mendis nudges it to square leg.
Outside off this time, wide one and Mendis makes an easy leave.
This one is close to the off stump, angling across. Mendis covers his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
Flatter ball, on top of off. Karunaratne stays back and punches it to covers.
Tries to toss one up but this is too full and on middle. Kept out.
Full and on middle. Karunaratne walks down the track and pushes it through covers for a run.
Flatter and on off, turning in. Mendis blocks it on the leg side.
Quicker one on middle. Mendis is solid in his defense.
Good bowling but Mendis is rock solid behind! Tossed up, outside off, spinning in. Mendis prods across and blocks it on the deck.
FOUR! Bowls it shorter and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne stands firm and slaps it past covers for a boundary.
Delivers it on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it out solidly.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne steers towards backward point for one.
Goes outside off again, Kusal Mendis shoulders arms at it.
Goes fuller and on off, Kusal Mendis drives it but finds the fielder at mid off.
On a length and on off, Kusal Mendis pushes it down the ground towards right of mid off and scampers for a quick single.
Fuller and outside leg with some turn, Kusal Mendis looks to give it a fine tickle but misses.
On middle this time, Kusal Mendis defends it towards short leg.
On middle with a hint of turn, this is defended towards the leg side.
Goes on middle again, Kusal Mendis eases it towards the short leg fielder.
Fuller and on off, Kusal Mendis blocks it towards the leg side.
Tossed up on off, this is nudged towards mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Kusal Mendis looks to flick it but miscues it towards the off side.
Outside off and slightly shorter, Kusal Mendis leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Kusal Mendis guides it towards backward point for one.
Good-length delivery, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Drives a fuller ball towards covers for one.
Goes shorter and down the middle, Dimuth Karunaratne ducks under it.
FOUR! Not a good start. A low full toss, Kusal Mendis times it well and flicks it past deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
On middle and fuller, Kusal Mendis works it towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Tossed-up delivery down the middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Fuller and just outside off turning it in, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it solidly.
Tossed up on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it but finds the fielder at backward square leg.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off with a hint of turn, Kusal Mendis defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis swivels and hits it towards backward square leg for one.
On off, defended out.
Goes fuller again and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it back towards Nathan Lyon.
FOUR! Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne dances down the track and flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, this is flicked towards square leg for one.

FOUR! Fifty up for the skipper. Fuller and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne uses his feet and smashes it past deep mid-wicket for a boundary. What a fifty this is from Karunaratne! He was short of runs but looks in fine form here. He will look to continue now.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne covers his line and defends it towards the leg side.
This one lands outside leg, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to flick it but misses.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne swings it but couldn't connect it well.
Steps down the track and then eases it down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Comes down the track again, done this quite a lot. Gets to the pitch and hence, he can play it against the turn to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, this is guided towards point for one.
A little too straight, Mendis clips it through square leg and takes one.
Another single! Good batting by the two out there. Runs coming now nicely for the hosts! On middle, this is worked wide of mid on for one.

Almost got done in by the dip! Swepson tosses it up, it ends up being a full toss. Karunaratne goes for the slog sweep but the ball dips in the end, it goes off the underedge towards mid-wicket for one.
On middle, blocked.
Pushes it through and bowls it on off, kept out.
Slightly shorter and outside off, this is cut to point.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Shorter and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne strokes it through covers and takes one.
FOUR! A full toss and Dimuth Karunaratne does not miss out! On the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket. Did not look to hit it too hard, just timed it.

Runs with the shot! On middle, this is worked to mid on for one. The 100-run stand is up. An outstanding parntership. Took their time at the start and now are cashing in. Need to go on though. They still trail by over 250.
Another run! On off, this is pushed to cover for one.
From over the wicket to the left-hander, it lands outside leg. Dimuth defends.
Now steps out, gets to the pitch of it and works it down to long on for one.
Two more to end! On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for a couple. 9 runs from the over.
Steps out but the length is shortened. Dimuth Karunaratne looks to defend but it hits the pad and lobs on the leg side.
The googly, outside off, Dimuth looks to push at it but is beaten.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth strokes it down to long off for one.
Good length and on off, blocked.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth Karunaratne drives it through covers for a single.
A bit short on the middle, Mendis goes down and pulls it to deep square leg for one.
Floated outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne punches it of his back foot to point.
Darts this one on the leg stump, Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards square leg for a run.
TURN AND BOUNCE! Tossed up on the off, Mendis tries to play at it but geats beaten by the turn and bounce and gets hit on his body.
Full and on off, knocked towards covers.

Huge shout for caught behind. Pat Cummins starts with a short ball on middle,angling away. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to flick it but misses and it goes past close to his gloves through to the keeper. They appeal but the finger stays down. Pat Cummins goes for the review but we can clearly see there is no edge. Ultra Edge confirms it. Review lost.
Full and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Goes for the yorker this time, on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne digs it out well to the leg side.
Goes full again down the leg side, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it towards fine leg for a single.
Good length outside off, Kusal Mendis blocks it off his front foot.
On a length and on off, Kusal Mendis pushes this to mid off.
Really good start by Head! He tosses it up, it drifts back in, lands and turns a touch. Defended.
On middle again, this is kept out well.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
A little too full and outside off, this is hit through covers for two.
On the stumps, kept out.
Shorter and outside off, Karunaratne guides it to point.
Good length and on off, Mendis defends.
Continues to pound it on a length and around off, blocked.
Slightly fuller and on off, Mendis pushes it to mid off.
Slightly fuller and on off, Mendis pushes it to mid off.
Fractionally short this time and on middle, blocked.
A single to end! On off, length, Mendis guides it towards point and gets to the other end.

Fifty for Mendis! A very solid innings from the Lankan number three and a much-needed one from his side. He should not throw it away now. Needs to make it big. Gets a gift to get there, it is short and on middle, it is pulled through square leg. The fielder runs to his right, dives and keeps it down to two.
Tossed up on middle, kept out.
Another one tossed up on off, blocked.
Sweeps this through square leg for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne works it towards mid on and takes one.
On a length and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne plays it with soft hands to covers for a single.
Back of a length outside off, Kusal Mendis late cuts it but could not get it past gully.
FOUR! Lovely Timing. This was full and onto the pads, Kusal Mendis just timed this one through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length on off, Kusal Mendis defends it to the off side.
A bit short outside off, Kusal Mendis pushes it straight to gully.
A single to end. Back of a length on off, Kusal Mendis gets on top of it and guides it through covers for a run.
FOUR! Well Played. This is slower through the air outside off, Kusal Mendis wait for the ball and just guides it towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Kusal Mendis drives it to mid off for a quick single.
Floated on off, defended well.
Quciker and fuller on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it through fine leg for a single.
A bit short on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis pulls it towards deep square leg for one.
Short again outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne cuts it but finds the fielder at backward point.
FOUR! Poor Delivery from Cummins. Bowls it short on the leg stump, Kusal Mendis just helps it on its way towards the deep square leg fence for another boundary.
Short again on leg, Kusal Mendis pulls it but this time it goes straight to fine leg. They cross.
Back of a length on off, angling in. Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it to point for a run.
Good length on middle and leg, Kusal Mendis glances it towards fine leg for a single.
Bangs it short and on middle, angling in towards the body. Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it off his back foot to the leg side.
Short again down the leg side, Dimuth Karunaratne works it through square leg for another run.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne comes down the track and defends it out.
Floated on middle, blocked out.
Flatter delivery on off, Dimuth Karunaratne knocks it of his back foot to silly mid off.
Good Delivery. Loopy and on leg, turning away. Dimuth Karunaratne tries to defend but gets a top edge but lands safely.
Floated outside leg, Dimuth Karunaratne nudges it to square leg for one.
Flatter and on off, defended well.
FOUR! Easy Pickings. Bowls it short and down the leg, Dimuth Karunaratne pulls it well towards the deep square leg fence for another boundary.
Short again on the leg stump, Dimuth Karunaratne controls his pull shot and pushes it to fine leg. They cross.
Bangs in a bouncer on middle, Kusal Mendis ducks underneath it.
Back of a length on middle, Kusal Mendis punches it of his back foot through mid-wicket for a single.
Cummins continues with his short ball tactics. Bowls it short but down the leg again, Dimuth Karunaratne guides it to fine leg for another easy single.
Tries the cutter this time. Bowls it on a length outside off, Kusal Mendis pushes it towards point. Australia are trying different things now to break this partnership.
Full-toss on the leg stump, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it towards long on for a run.
A bit short outside off, Kusal Mendis cuts it off his back foor through point for a run.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it well.
Tossed up again on middle, blocked out.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth Karunaratne moves across and flicks it to long on for a single.
Nicely Bowled. Tossed up outside off, spinning in. Kusal Mendis does well to defend it out.
Full-toss to start with, Dimuth Karunaratne goes for the drive but mistimes it to mid off.
FOUR! Loose delivery. Short and on the middle stump, Dimuth Karunaratne pulls it through square leg for another boundary.
Floated on middle, defended out.

OUT! THREE REDS! Dimuth Karunaratne was on his way back after watching the first replay. He knew he made a mistake by taking the review. Misreads the length and it is Swepson who strikes in the first over of his new spell and it is a much-needed wicket. This is on middle, pushed through. Dimuth Karunaratne goes back and looks to flick, he is late in getting his bat down, misses and is hit on the pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Dimuth Karunaratne reviews but in vain. The superb partnership is broken. Can this be the opening the Aussies needed?
Tossed up on leg, this is defended towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller one down the middle, Angelo Mathews defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fuller one outside off, Kusal Mendis gets on his knees and drives it past extra cover fence for a boundary.
On off again, Kusal Mendis punches it towards long on for one.
Tossed up outside off, Angelo Mathews looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A slight appeal and they decide not to review it.
Bowls it on middle, this is defended towards the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Angelo Mathews flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fuller and down the middle, this is flicked towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up delivery, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is defended towards the vacant short leg region.
Keeps bowling it on middle, Angelo Mathews defends it towards the leg side.
On off, Angelo Mathews eases it towards short covers.
Fuller one on middle, Angelo Mathews flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
A maiden from Mitchell Swepson. On middle, Angelo Mathews defends it out solidly.
Tosses it outside off, Kusal Mendis guides it towards covers for one.
On off, kept out.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Angelo Mathews eases it towards gully and takes a quick single.
Fuller and outside off, Kusal Mendis waits for the ball and punches it towards extra covers for one.
Bowls it on middle, Angelo Mathews defends it solidly.
Tossed up on middle, Kusal Mendis flicks it towards square leg for one.
Fuller and on off turning it away, Angelo Mathews guides it towards the fielder at gully.
Outside off with some turn, Angelo Mathews leaves it. The keeper fails to collect it as well as it races towards backward point. They cross.
Goes outside off again, Kusal Mendis cuts it towards point for a brace.
On middle, defended out.
Fuller and down the middle, Kusal Mendis defends it back towards the bowler.
Starts fuller and on off, Angelo Mathews defends it back towards Mitchell Starc.
On a length and down the leg side, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Kusal Mendis defends it solidly.
Back of a length and on off, Kusal Mendis waits for the ball and steers it towards backward point for one.
On a length and on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it away solidly.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Angelo Mathews shoulders arms at it.
On off and fuller, this is flicked towards the leg side. Kusal Mendis wanted a single but was sent back.
Tossed up on off, Kusal Mendis steers it towards covers.
On off, Kusal Mendis drives it towards extra covers for a single.
Shorter and on off, Angelo Mathews waits for the ball and punches it towards covers for one.
Bowls it on leg, Kusal Mendis flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards square leg for one.
A fuller ball, outside off. Mathews blocks it out on the front foot.
On a length and outside off, angling across. Mathews prods and keeps it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Mathews shoulders arms to it.
A length ball on off. Mathews taps it to point and calls for a quick single. He hits it straight to the fielder there and Mendis turns it down wisely.
Outside off. Left alone.
Mathews will keep the strike what could possibly be the last over! Length ball, on top of off. Mathews opens the back of the bat and dabs it to third man for a single.
Too full and on leg.  Mathews blocks it out.
Flatter and around off. Mathews rocks back and punches it back to the bowler.
Sliding on the pads. Mathews keeps it out on the leg side.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Mathews prods and defends it out.
Tossed up again. Mathews negotiates it well.
That is the last ball! Fuller and on off. Mathews drives it straight to mid off. That will be Stumps on Day 2.
Tossed up, outside off. Mendis shuffles across and blocks it on the deck.
Drops it short and outside off. Mendis punches off the back foot to covers.
Good bunce there, shorter and outside off. Mendis punches it uppishly but in the safe cover region.
Fleasedoated, full and on middle, eased to mid on.

Mendis survives and he was inches away from walking back. Superb bowling from Lyon! Serves it on a good length, outside off and it spins in sharply. Mendis is rooted on the back foot as he looks to fend away but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge shout for LBW but not given! Skipper, Lyon and Carey have a chat and Australia take the review. Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows umpire's call on wickets hitting. Mendis survives. Nonetheless, a good review from the Aussie.
Tossed up on off. Defended out.
Length ball, around off. Mathews blocks it to covers.
Fuller ball, around the 5th stump channel. Mathews covers his stumps and blocks it.
A bumper, around middle and leg. Mathews sits under it.
Overpitched, outside off. Mathews drives it straight to mid on.
Too straight on the pads, flicked behind square on the leg side for a single.
On a length and outside off. Mendis guides it to point for one more.
Swing and a miss! Tossed up, outside off, hits the deck and spins in. Mendis looks to sweep but misses.

OUT! LBW! Turn does the trick as Lyon gets the breakthrough! Australia wanted an early wicket and they have one here. Brilliant from Lyon once again. Nicely flights this one, full and outside off, spinning sharply in. Mendis tries to stay back as he looks to work it away but it spins sharply and pings him on the pads. A huge shout for LBW and up goes the finger. It looked plumb but Kusal Mendis reviews it tough. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Kusal Mendis has to go. Australia will be happy that the pitch is helping the bowlers as well.
Fuller and outside off. Blocked out.
Pushes it full and outside off, turning in. Chandimal prods to defend but gets an inside edge to square leg.
Flatter and on off. Chandimal blocks on the back foot.
Tossed up on off, angling in. Kept out.
Length ball on off, nips back in. Mathews dead bats it.
Length ball from wide of the crease and angling on off. Mathews turns it to mid-wicket.
A sharp bouncer on middle. Angelo leaves it alone.
Short of a length on the hips. Mathews bunts it to deep square leg for a single.

An appeal but it clearly came off the pads. Short in length again, angling on the pads. Chandimal tries to flick but misses and it goes off the pads and lobs in the hands of the man at short leg who puts up an appeal but nothing given.
Short of a length, outside off, jags away slightly. Chandimal looks to push but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and outside off, swept to square leg for a single.
FOUR! First boundary of the Day! Tossed up, outside off. Chandimal skips down but hits off the toe end and past covers for a boundary.
SIX! Counterattack from Chandimal! A loopy ball, outside off. Chandimal dances down again and smashes it over extra cover for a biggie.
Shorter and spinning on middle. Blocked solidly.
Too full and on middle, played back to Lyon.
Short and outside off, no spin this time. Chandimal slaps it to point.
On the pads, tucked to square leg for one.
On a length, slanting on middle. Chandimal wrists it past mid-wicket for one more.
Length ball, on top of off. Mathews nudges it straight to short leg.
Outside off, on a length at 131 kph. Mathews keeps it out.
EDGED AND FOUR! Back of a length and around middle and leg. Mathews looks to pull with soft hands but gets a top edge, over the keeper and into the fence.
This one stays a bit low on off. Mathews works it to covers.
Quicker, fuller and on middle. Chandimal steps across and blocks it out.

Two byes! Missed everything! Beautiful from Lyon! He is enjoying the conditions now! Flighted, around off, it lands and turns sharply in. Dinesh Chandimal comes down the track and looks to heave across but misses and the ball whizzes past the leg stump. It goes well away from Carey as well and behind him for two runs.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up on middle. Chandimal defends it.
Tossed up on middle. Chandimal sweeps, not off the middle and hits it wide of leg slip for a single.
FOUR! Well played! Floated, around off. Mathews reverse sweeps it to third man for a boundary.
Full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
Full again on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to short covers.
On a length outside off, holds its line. Dinesh Chandimal offers no shot.
Fuller and on middle, angling in. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to square leg for a run. A no ball is called for over stepping
Good length outside off, Angelo Mathews lets it go to the keeper.
A bit short on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews plays a slighly uppish pull shot towards deep sqaure leg for a run.
On a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it from his back foot to short covers.
Floated on off, Angelo Mathews comes down the pitch and defends it to the off side.
Tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews goes down and plays the sweep towards deep square leg for a couple. The fielder does well to stop it in the deep.
Floated on off, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, Mathews leans forward and defends it.
Gets hit on the helmet. Tossed up outside off, turning in. Angelo Mathews goes for the sweep but gets beaten by the bounce and gets hit on the grill.
Loopy delivery on middle, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and flicks it through square leg for one.
Starts with a flatter delivery on off, Angelo Mathews blocks it out.
Full and on middle, Angelo Mathews flicks it straight to short mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Angelo Mathews moves across and eases it to long on for a single.
Full on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it well.
Tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up again on off, Dinesh Chandimal this time pushes it past short mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Tossed up on middle, turning in. Dinesh Chandimal sweeps it but could not get past backward short leg.
Floated onto the stumps, Dinesh Chandimal steps out and drives it straight to short mid on
Slower through the air, Dinesh Chandimal goes for the sweep but could not connect and gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps it through square leg for a run.
Full and on middle, Angelo Mathews works it through square leg for another single.
Tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it out.
Full and wide outside off, Dinesh Chandimal guides it towards point for a run.
Flatter and outside off, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and works it to long on for a run.
Tossed up on off, blocked out.
Quicker and flatter on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it towards long on for a single,
Floated on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Beautiful Shot. This is tossed up outside off, Angelo Mathews waits for it and plays a handsome drive through covers for a boundary.
Floated on off, Dinesh Chandimal steps out and defends it down the pitch.
On middle, Dinesh Chandimal is solid in his defense.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal goes down and sweeps it to deep square leg for a run.
Darts this one on middle, Angelo Mathews defends it well.
Floated on middle, drifting in. Angelo Mathews walks down the pitch and knocks it to short leg. He adjusted well to play this one.
Full and on middle, Angelo Mathews pushes it through square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Angelo Mathews digs it to mid off.
FOUR! Risk and reward for Mathews. This is tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews lofts it over the mid on fielder for a boundary,
Full and on middle, Angelo Mathews drives it straight to mid off.
Slower through the air outside off, turning away. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
Floated on middle, with a hint of turn again. Angelo Mathews blocks it out.

Flatter and quicker on leg, Angelo Mathews tries to play at it but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls towards backward square leg. They cross. This brings up the 50-run partnership between these two.
A bit too full on off, Angelo Mathews eases it to long on for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Dinesh Chandimal mistimes his sweep towards deep square leg but still gets a single.
Floated on middle, Angelo Mathews comes down the pitch and knocks it straight to short mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, turning in. Angelo Mathews uses his feet again but fails to connect and get hits on his pads.

Tossed up outside off, drifting in. Angelo Mathews tries to play the reverse sweep but misses the ball completely. The Australians appeal for an LBW but the finger stays down. Pat Cummins goes for the review but the Ulta Edge shows a spike, an inside edge on it. Mathews survives but Australia lose their review.
Full and on middle, Angelo Mathews sweeps it through square leg for another single.
Tossed up on middle, Angelo Mathews plays a solid defense.
Bowls a full toss on leg, Angelo Mathews drives it well but it is well stopped at short mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, turning away. Angelo Mathews knocks it to short mid off.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Tossed up on off, Angelo Mathews defends it to the off side.
Full-toss on middle, Angelo Mathews comes down the pitch and drives it firmly towards long on for a brace.

NOT OUT! Tossed up on off, turning in. Dinesh Chandimal comes down the track and tries to play it to the off side but gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball goes in the air off his pads to Travis Head at silly point. They appeal for bat pad but the finger stays down. The batters get across for a leg bye while the fielders where celebrating.  Australia takes the review but ultraedge shows nothing and ball tracking favours the batsman as well. Australia loses their last review.
A bit short outside off, Angelo Mathews pushes it from his back foot towards mid-wicket for a run.
Full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps it through square leg for a run.
A bit too full on off, Angelo Mathews plays it with soft hands to point and get across for the single.
Full and on off, drilled down to long on for a single.
Shorter, spinning in. Mathews fends it to square leg.
Tossed up on leg, this is flicked mid on.
On off this time, Dinesh Chandimal steers it to mid off for one.
Fuller one again, Angelo Mathews hits it but straight towards the left of the bowler.
A low full toss, Angelo Mathews guides it to long on for one.
Bowls it outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches it towards covers and rotates the strike.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Angelo Mathews defends it solidly.
Fuller one on middle, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps as it bounces off the fielder at short leg.
On off with some turn, Dinesh Chandimal looks to play at it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the off side. Leg bye taken.
Fuller one on middle, Angelo Mathews sweeps it towards square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it solidly.
On off, kept out.
Shorter one on middle, Dinesh Chandimal punches it towards the fielder at mid on.
Bowls it on off, this is guided towards point for one.
Tossed up with some turn, Dinesh Chandimal looks to defend it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and rolls towards his toes.
On off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Goes fuller and down the middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it away.
This one lands down the leg side, Angelo Mathews hits it towards mid on for one.
On off and much fuller in length, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards the off side for a quick single.
Goes 'round the wicket and bowls it on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it towards mid on.
Fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards short mid-wicket fielder.
On middle and fuller in length, Dinesh Chandimal defends it back towards the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Fuller and down the middle, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps it towards the fielder at deep square leg. They cross.
Goes outside off angling it into the batter, Angelo Mathews defends it towards short leg.
Starts with a length delivery outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
On a length and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal defends it away.
Touch fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to push it but misses. The ball just aired past his blade and into the gloves of the keeper.
Fuller one on off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to play at it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards backward square leg. They rotate the strike.
Bowls it on a full length, Angelo Mathews defends it well.
Fuller one on off, Angelo Mathews flicks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
Goes fuller and wide outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
On a length and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal punches it towards the fielder at mid off.
This one lands outside off, Dinesh Chandimal shoulders arms at it.
Outside off again with some extra bounce, Dinesh Chandimal gets in two minds but lets it go in the end.
Fuller one on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
Goes fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight towards the fielder at short covers.
Goes outside off, Angelo Mathews guides it towards the off side and takes a quick single. The fielder makes a direct hit at the non-strikers' end but Angelo Mathews was well safe.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball down the middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it towards short covers.
Touch fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to play at it but misses.
Goes outside off again, Dinesh Chandimal punches it towards the fielder at short covers.
Fuller one on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it towards short covers where the fielder makes a diving stop. No runs.
On a length and down the leg side, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On off and fuller in length, Dinesh Chandimal guides it towards the mid off fielder.
Fuller one again, this is defended towards the left of mid on.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Dinesh Chandimal eases it to short covers.
On a length and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Bowls it down the leg side, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards fine leg for one again.

On a length and on off, Angelo Mathews blocks it as the ball bounces back in front of him. He thinks to take it into his hands but leaves it in the end. Angelo Mathews and Mitchell Starc exchange smiles.
On off and on middle, defended.
Shorter one on middle, Angelo Mathews ducks underneath it.
This one lands fuller in length, Angelo Mathews defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on leg, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
On a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal shoulders arms at it. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Tossed up on middle. Mathews gets back and defends it out.
Tosses it up, around off. Mathews covers his off stump and defends it out.

Too full and angling around middle and off. Angelo Mathews gets on his knee to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but not given. Australia do not have a review. Impact might be an issue there.
Fuller and on off. Blocked out.
Another appeal for LBW but turned down! Tosses it up, quicker this time, around off. Mathews takes a couple of steps down and tries to block but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Fifty for Angelo Mathews! The senior man has stepped up for his team! A fine knock from Mathews! Flatter and on middle. He tucks it to square leg for a single. 38th Test fifty!
On a length and outside off. Mathews punches away from the body and past mid off for a single. Sri Lanka trail by 99 now.

Four leg byes! A huge appeal for LBW again but the umpire is not interested! A length ball, angling on top of off. Mathews tries to flick near his pads but misses and gets on the pads. Australia are appealing and they fail to keep an eye on the ball as it races away to the fence. The replay later shows it was umpire's call on wickets hitting.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally, Australia break the stand. They were the better team after the break and they get the reward! It was similar like the previous ball. Length and around off. Mathews is rooted as he looks to flick across his pads but gets an inside edge onto the pads and it lobs nicely for Marnus Labuschagne at short leg. An appeal and Australia celebrate. Angelo Mathews goes right after making his fifty.
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Bowls it on off, this is defended towards mid off.
On a length and down the middle, Kamindu Mendis defends it back towards the bowler.
Shorter in length from Mitchell Starc. Kamindu Mendis ducks underneath it.
Tossed up on off. Chandimal drops it to covers for a single.

Shorter and drifting outside off. Mendis looks to cut but misses. There is a stifled appeal for caught behind but not given. Carey removes the bails so the umpire checks for stumping. The foot is grounded. Not out.
Full and angling on off. Defended out.
Flatter and outside off, hint of spin. Mendis punches it to covers.
FOUR! Mendis is off the mark! Drops it short and outside off. Mendis rocks back and cuts it hard past point for a boundary.
Angles a length ball on middle. Mendis solidly blocks it.
A length ball on the pads, at 140 clicks. Chandimal fails to flick it away.
On a length and just outside off, punched to covers.
A sharp bouncer on middle. Chandimal has to get big to defend this out.
Touch fuller and on middle. Chandimal forces it to mid on. Australia have certainly come with full batteries. They have been brilliant so far.

A huge, huge appeal for caught behind but not given! Australia are not happy and for a time, Mitchell Starc forget they do not have a review. There was a sound though. Shorter and around off, angling across. Chandimal in the last minute tries to wrist it away on the off side but seems to miss it, Carey takes it and everyone appeals but not given. The replay shows there was a spike. Dinesh Chandimal gets a lifeline. How important were those review which Australia burned easily!
FOUR! A length ball, outside off. Chandimal drives it through mid off for a boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Shorter and outside off, turning away, cut to point.
Shorter again, outside off. Mendis punches it wide of point for a single.
Tossed up, around off, pushed to covers for a single.
Too full and on middle. Blocked out.
A loopy ball on off. Mendis watchfully blocks it.
A length ball, slanting on middle. Chandimal stays back and plays it back to Starc.
Around middle and leg. Chandimal nudges it to mid-wicket and takes a sharp single.
Tries a short one but serves it down the leg side. Mendis lets it through.
On a length and top of off. Mendis guides it to point for one more.
No run.
FOUR! Smashed away! Too full and angling outside off. Chandimal thumps it over mid off for a boundary. Sri Lanka now trail by 78 runs.
Tossed up on off, nicely defended by Kamindu Mendis.
Flatter and on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it through covers for one.
Comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it, gently pushes it to covers.
Pushes it through but it lands on middle, Kamindu Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Slightly shorter and on off, Mendis pushes it to covers. Not a lot of turn for Lyon as of now. The wicket has held up well.
Quicker and outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Angled into the pads, Dinesh Chandimal works it through square leg and takes one.
A bumper now to Kamindu! It is evaded.
Tip and run! Shorter and on off, Mendis plays it towards cover for one.
Easy pickings! Just for one though! On the pads, this is clipped down to fine leg for one.
Yet another one which is a little too straight, it is clipped through square leg for one.
Shorter and on middle, Chandimal defends.
On off, blocked.
Slows it up and lands it on middle, blocked.
Shortish and on off, Mendis guides it to point.
FLatter and it drifts back in from outside off, Mendis keeps it out nicely.
On middle, defended.
A dot to end a maiden! On the stumps, blocked.
Lands safe! This is on a length, it lands outside off and jags back in. Chandimal looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It lobs back towards the bowler but lands safe.
Angled into the pads, Chandimal plays it down to fine leg for one more.
Another one on a length and around off, defended nicely.
Shorter and on off, Mendis guides it through point and gets to the other end.

FOUR! EDGY! Sri Lanka won't mind though. When you shalsh, slash hard and that is what Chandimal did! Shorter and outside off, he goes after it, it flies off the top edge over the slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Almost! Green really bent his back on this one, it is shorter and around off, comes back in and also zips through. Chandimal is beaten as he tries to put bat on ball.
Well bowled! Sees Mendis come down the track and shortens the length. Mendis does well to block it.
Almost chops it on! Outside off, a little too close to cut. Mendis looks to do so but gets an underedge, it hits Carey on his boot.
Outside off, left alone.
A little too full, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Loopy ball on off, Chandimal defends.
Flatter and around off, Chandimal defends it.
On the off pole, shorter, this is pushed to covers.
Short and on middle, Mendis works it to md-wicket.
Bangs it short and on the body! Mendis swings hard but misses.
On middle, this is played to mid on for one.
Fuller and on off, Chandimal strokes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Shorter and on off, defended.
This is very full and very wide outside off, Chandimal plooks to play a pre-determined sweep but misses it completely.
Nicely flighted and lands it on off, this one turns in. Defended.
On middle, blocked.
FOUR! That is swept brilliantly! On off, Chandimal goes down on one knee and gets on top of the bounce, sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Flatter and on off, Chandimal blocks it out.
On the stumps, Chandimal defends.
Sharp bumper, really uses a lot of shoulder strength, gets it to bounce nicely. Mendis evades it.
Yet another short one and on middle, Mendis sways out of the way.
Back of a length and on off, Mendis guides it to point and takes one.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
On off, blocked.
Three more to end the over! Shorter and on off, Chandimal pushes it through covers for three.
Tossed up outside off, Dinesh Chandimal goes for the drive but inside edges onto his pads and it goes to the air but lands safely.
Floated on middle, Dinesh Chandimal leans on to play at but again gets an inside edge onto his pads, it goes just past short leg.
Full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal sweeps it to fine leg for a run.
Full on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker on off, Mendis pushes it to covers.
Tossed up outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Flatter delivery on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to covers for a run.
Full and on middle and off, Mendis defends it well.
FOUR! Nice Shot. Tossed up on off, Mendis comes down the pitch and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
Floated on middle, Mendis blocks it to short mid-wiclet.
Too full outside off, Mendis digs it through point for a brace.
Full and on off, blocked off.
Tossed up outside off, Dinesh Chandimal moves across and paddle sweeps it to fine leg for couple of runs.
Floated on middle, defended out.
Tossed up outside off, Dinesh Chandimal steps out and knocks it to te off side.
Fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to extra cover.
A bit short on middle, Dinesh Chandimal goes down and works it to deep square leg for one.

CLOSE CALL! This is a bit short outside off, Mendis pushes it to covers. He calls for the run and his partner responds. But mid way through there is hesitation and he is sent back. If it was a direct hit at the striker's end he was a goner.
Full-toss on leg, Dinesh Chandimal eases it to long on for a run.
Full and outside off, Mendis uses his feet and digs it short covers.
Short and outside off, Mendis punches of his back foot through point for one.
Floated on middle, blocked out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal plays a solid front foot defense.
Full and on middle and leg, Mendis knocks it to short mid-on.
Slower through the air outside off, turning away a bit. Mendis pushes it to short third man.
Floated outside off, Mendis punches it to covers.
FOUR! A bit short outside off, Kamindu Mendis waits for it and cuts it past the 1st slip to the third man fence for a boundary.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated on off, defended well.
Full and onto the pads, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Mendis digs it straight to the bowler.
Full and on middle, Mendis uses his feet again and inside edges it towards fine leg for one.
A bit short down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to long on for one.
Slower through the air outside off, turning in. Mendis defends it well.
Tossed up outside off, Mendis comes down to the pitch of the ball and drives it through covers for a single.
Loopy delivery drifting onto the pads, Mendis flicks it straight to square leg.
Floated on middle, Mendis steps out and defends down the pitch.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Mendis tries to play the cut but gets beaten by the late turn.It just goes past the outside edge of his willow.
Floated on off, knocked towards point.
Flatter delivery on off, Mendis defends it well.
Darts this one down the leg side, Mendis tries to flick it but misses.
Full and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal bunts it through mid-wicket for a run.

A huge shout for LBW. This is floated outside off, turning in. Mendis tries to defend it but gets hit on his pads. The Aussies appeal but the finger stays down. The replay shows there was an inside edge.
Bowls the googly this time, on off. Mendis guides it short third man.
A bit short on off, Mendis cuts it backward point.
Full and on off, Mendis comes down the track and drives it firmly but silly point got in the way and they get a single.
Too full on leg, Chandimal digs it out well.
Tossed up on middle, Mendis uses his feet and lofts it to mid on.
Floated on off, defended out.
A bit short on off, sliding in. Mendis negotiates it well.
Floated on off, blocked out.
A bit short outside off, Mendis punches it to backward point for one.
Tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal steps out to defend but gets a thick inside edge and ball goes to short leg on the bounce.
FOUR! This is well connected. Bowls a fuller and down the middle, Kamindu Mendis plays a reverse sweep towards backward point for a boundary.
On off, this is played towards mid off for a quick single. Good running between the wickets.
Delivers it on leg, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller one down the middle, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards the off side.
Fuller again but wide outside leg, Dinesh Chandimal moves to his leg and defends it with his pads.
Tossed-up delivery, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards mid on for one.
Tossed up outside off, swept away towards deep square leg for one.
Slower through the air around leg, turning away. Mendis offers no shot at it.
Floated on middle, Mendis blocks it out to the off side.
Tossed up on leg, Mendis lets it hit his pads.
Similar to the previous delivery. Mendis again uses his pads to keep the ball out.
Floated on middle, Mendis leans on and defends it down the pitch.
Starts with a length ball outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
A bit fuller outside off, Dinesh Chandimal offers no shot.
FOUR! Clever shot. This is too full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it firmly past short covers for a boundary.
Full again outside off, sticks onto the pitch. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to mid off.
Good length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to silly mid on.
Full again on off, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to silly mid on.
Tossed up on leg, Mendis defends it onto his pads.
Beautifully bowled. This is slower through the air around leg, Mendis looks to play at ait but gets beaten by the turn and bounce.
Flatter on leg, Mendis lets it hit his pads.
TOUGH CHANCE! Tossed up on middle, turning away. Mendis tries to push at it but gets a thick outside edge and it goes just wide of Steven Smith at first slip and goes to third man. They get two runs.
Full and on leg, Mendis steps out and clips it to mid on for a run.
Full and outside off, swept away through square leg for one.
Length and on off, left alone.
On a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it towards deep point for a run.
Good length on middle and off, Kamindu Mendis flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Too full outside off, Dinesh Chandimal digs it straight to mid off.
Got the length right this time. This on off, shaping away a bit. Dinesh Chandimal lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Bangs this one short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it over point for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Dinesh Chandimal moves across and works it through mid-wicket for a run.
Floated around leg, Mendis defends it to short leg.
Slower through the air on leg, turning away. Mendis tries to flick it but misses and gets hit onto the pads. Shouts for LBW but the umpire is not interested.
A bit short on middle, Mendis flicks it through square leg for a run.
Full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it through mid-wicket for one.
Floated on middle, Mendis blocks it out.
Back of a length outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it hard towards deep cover point for a single.
Fuller and on off, Kamindu Mendis drives it but could not get it past short covers.
A bit short on middle and leg, Kamindu Mendis awkwardly knocks it to the leg side. They get a single.
On a length and on off, angling away. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
A bit full outside off, angling away again. Dinesh Chandimal covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length outside off, another easy leave for Dinesh Chandimal.
Floated on leg, Mendis uses his feet and pushes it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on leg, Mendis uses his pads to keep it out.
FOUR! Classy Shot. A bit short by Lyon on middle, Kamindu Mendis goes back on his crease and punches it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up around leg, blocked out to the off side.

STUMPING CHANCE! Lyon gives it air on leg, spins a long way in. Kamindu Mendis steps out but gets beaten by the turn and bounce. Alex Carey could not collect the ball and another stumping chance goes begging.
Floated on middle, Mendis defends it well.
FOUR! Scores level! A length ball, angling way outside off. Chandimal smashes it over covers for a boundary.
On a length and outside off. Chandimal shuffles across and blocks it.
Touch fuller and outside off. Chandimal hits it to covers.
A short ball, around off. Chandimal sits under it.
Sri Lanka lead by a run now! On a length and outside off. Chandimal carves it to point for a run.
Short again but down the leg side. Mendis ducks under it.
Full and on middle. Chandimal blocks it.
Tossed up, this lands on off and spins away. Chandimal shoulders arms to it.
This one spins but it is outside off. Left alone.
Flighted, outside off, driven to mid off for a single.
Too much flight this time, on the pads, eased down to long on for a single.
Flighted full toss on off. Chandimal drives it to mid off for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Chandimal drives it straight but Cummins gets a big left-hand to it.
On a length and on middle. Chandimal tucks it to square leg for one. The 100-run partnership is up between these two.
Short one, climbing on the batter. Mendis dabs it to the gully region for a single.

Overthrow! A length ball, slower and outside off. Chandimal steers it straight to the fielder at third slip. The fielder has an unnecessary shy at the striker's end but misses and ends up giving an easy single.
Short and on off. Kept out.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Back of a length and on off. Mendis punches off the back foot through covers for a boundary. He moves to 49.
Tossed up, outside off, driven to short cover.
Chandimal again hits this full ball to covers.
Outside off, turning away. Left alone.
Marnus Labuschagne is getting some drift here, fuller and on off. Defended out.
On middle. Chandimal gets on the front foot to defend.
Shorter and on the pads. Chandimal nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a single to end the over.
Flatter and outside off, cut straight to point.
Tossed up on middle. Chandimal prods and defends it.
Floated, full and on off. Chandimal works it to backward point.
Too full and on off. Chandimal drills it to mid-wicket who runs to his left to stop it.
Flatter and outside off. Chandimal pushes it to mid off for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Maiden fifty for Kamindu Mendis! tossed up on middle. Mendis comes down the track and eases it to long on for a single. His teammates are on their feet to appreciate the knock.
Full toss on middle, Mendis forces it to long on for one.
Tossed up, outside off, moving away. Chandimal has a big swing trying to go over covers but mistimes it to deep point for one more.
Shorter and outside off. Mendis shuffles across and blocks it.
Angles a full ball on middle. Mendis watchfully defends it.
Was that a chance? Nope, went on a bounce! A big full toss on middle. Mendis skips down and tries to heave but plays off the inner half and to mid-wicket.It went to Warner on a bounce.  A single.
On off, kept out.
Full and outside off. Mendis pushes it to point. He wants a single but is sent back.
Pitching outside leg on the pads. Mendis pads it away.
FOUR! Well timed! Shorter and angling across, on off. Mendis rocks back and punches it to covers, beats the fielder diving to his right and it races to the fence.
Short again, cut to point.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Quicker one on middle. Mendis waits and dabs it on the off side.
Flatter and on middle, punched to covers by Chandimal.
On middle, fuller, defended solidly.
Tossed up, outside off. Chandimal pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
Fuller and outside off. Mendis uses his feet and reaches to it as he pushes to covers.
Slants a full on off, hit back to the bowler.
Shorter and around off. Mendis hits it with the spin to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on middle, spinning across. Mendis watchfully defends it to point.
On the pads, swept behind square on the leg side for one run.
Flatter, outside off, turning in. Chandimal skips down to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to short leg and he rushes back into his crease.
FOUR! Chandimal moves to 94! Fuller and outside off. Chandimal sweeps it wide of backward square leg for a boundary.
Too full, flighted and on off. Chandimal keeps it out.
Around off. Chandimal comes down the pitch and drills it to long on for one.
On off, kept out.
Down the leg side. Chandimal misses his flick.
Flatter ball on middle. Chandimal works it through covers for one more.
Shorter and spinning into the batter, hit to long on for a single.
A leggie, full and outside off. Chandimal pushes to cover.
A googly now, full and outside off. Chandimal steps forward to defend it. Sri Lanka lead by 31 runs.
Tossed up around off, this is punched towards short covers.
Fuller and down the middle, Kamindu Mendis sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it well.
Bowls it on off, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards the off side and scampers for a quick single.

Fuller one with some turn, Kamindu Mendis looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A slight appeal but the finger stays down. Australia is out of their reviews as well so they cannot review.
On middle, defended out.
Fuller and on middle, defended towards short covers.
Loopy one on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it well off his front foot.
This one lands fuller as well, Dinesh Chandimal eases it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal slaps it but finds the fielder at deep point. They cross.
Fuller one outside off turning it in, Kamindu Mendis looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his pads.
A googly on off, Kamindu Mendis eases it towards the off side.
Fuller one on off, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards mid on for one. He moves to 99 now.
On off, this is played towards point.
Outside off and fuller, Kamindu Mendis eases it to covers for one. This brings up 400 for Sri Lanka and they lead by 36 runs now!

Century for Dinesh Chandimal. His 13th Test hundred and 2nd against Australia. This one lands fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards covers and takes one. Excellent from Dinesh Chandimal and he did it when his team needed it desperately!
On off, defended out.
Bowls it outside off, this is eased towards the off side.
Fuller and on off, Dinesh Chandimal guides it to covers for one.

OUT! BOWLED! Australia finally has a breakthrough. This one lands way outside off, fuller and turns back in sharply and knocks over the middle and leg pole. Kamindu Mendis completely mistimes his slog sweep and ends up getting a slight bottom edge. Kamindu Mendis goes after a very good innings.
Fuller and outside off, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
On off, defended out.
Fuller one outside off, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards the off side.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it towards short leg.
Tossed up on off, Niroshan Dickwella punches it towards mid on.
Goes fuller and on off, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it towards the fielder at leg gully.
Bowls it on off, Niroshan Dickwella eases it towards covers.
Fuller one on off, Niroshan Dickwella guides it towards the mid on fielder.
Another fuller delivery and on middle, Niroshan Dickwella defends it back towards the bowler.
A single to end the over. Tossed up on middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it towards square leg and takes a single.
Tossed up outside off, Niroshan Dickwella eases it towards short covers.

Fuller one on middle, Niroshan Dickwella looks to reverse sweep it but gets a top edge and the ball carries towards covers. There was no fielder at covers and Niroshan Dickwella gets a lucky escape. They cross.
On off, played towards the off side.
Fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards leg side for one.
Shorter and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal punches it towards mid off.
Goes outside off again, Dinesh Chandimal eases it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, this is defended back towards the bowler.
On off, this is eased towards covers for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nathan Lyon gets his second wicket. Shorter and on off, slower too, Niroshan Dickwella dances down the track and looks to loft it but doesn't get the power right. It goes off the bottom half of the bat and towards mid on and straight into the hands of Pat Cummins.
Howout: c Pat Cummins b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: On off, kept out.
Fuller and down the leg side, Ramesh Mendis eases it towards silly mid on.
On middle and fuller, Dinesh Chandimal defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller again, Dinesh Chandimal nudges it towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Fuller and quicker too, Ramesh Mendis looks to block it but gets a bottom edge and bounces towards short leg.
Tossed up on off, this is defended towards point.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Ramesh Mendis steers it towards short covers and straight towards the fielder.
Fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal guides it towards mid off.
On middle this time, Dinesh Chandimal eases it back towards Nathan Lyon.
This one lands on leg, Dinesh Chandimal hits it towards long on for a single.
Slightly shorter, Ramesh Mendis punches it towards mid on and gets off the mark.
Bowls it on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards leg side for one.
Fuller one on middle, Ramesh Mendis flicks it as it bounces back off the fielder at short leg.
Tossed up outside off with some turn, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it to point for one. They lead by 50 now.
Another one outside off turning it away, Ramesh Mendis looks to play it but gets an outside edge as it rolls towards the fielder at gully.
A low full toss, Ramesh Mendis hits it to the left of the bowler who does well to get it. Ramesh Mendis wanted a single but was sent back.
On middle, this is flicked towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Quicker one on middle, Ramesh Mendis covers his line and blocks it well.
Slightly shorter outside off, Ramesh Mendis looks to play at it but misses.
Full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to mid off.
Tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal tries to loft it over mid off but does not get the power right, Luckily for him it just clears mid off and they get a single.
Floated on middle, Mendis blocks it to the leg side.
On middle, Mendis defends it well.
A bit short outside off, Mendis cuts from his back foot to wide of mid off for a run.
Floaed on middle, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it out.
Tossed up on off, Ramesh Mendis goes for the slog-sweep but gets a top edge and it travels towards deep mid-wicket. They get a couple.
On middle, blocket out.
BEATEN! Slower through the air on middle, turning away. Ramesh Mendis tries to defend but the ball goes just past his outside edge.
Too full on middle, Mendis digs it out.
A leggie on off, Mendis defends it from his front foot.
Nicely Bowled. This lands on middle, turns away sharply. Mendis tries to play at it but gets nowhere near it,
Floated on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to fine leg,
Tossed up on middle, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up and on off, Dinesh Chandimal drills it to long on for one.

NOT OUT! This one lands short on middle, turning away to the leg side. Ramesh Mendis tries to pull at it but misses it completely and it goes to the keeper. They appeal for the caught behind and the umpire raises his finger. Ramesh Mendis takes the review and we can clearly see in Ultra Edge that there was no edge.
Tossed up on off, Mendis guides it to covers for one.
Angled in to off, Dinesh Chandimal defends it well.
Another stumping chance missed. Swepson darts it full down the leg, Mendis comes down the track but misses the ball. Alex Carey could not collect the ball and lets go of the stumping chance.
Floated on middle, Mendis defends it.
Tossed up on leg, Mendis leans on to block it.
Another big leggie, on middle. Mendis jabs it to point.
Darts this on leg, Mendis sweeps it to fine leg.
Full and on middle, swept away for a single,
Short on middle, spinning away. Mendis pushes it to cover point for a run.
Short again outside off, kept low. Chandimal tries to cut it but plays over it.
Full and on off, Dinesh Chandimal drills it to long off for a run.
Full and on leg, pushed to mid-wicket.
Tossed up outside off, Mendis blocks it out.
Short outside off, Mendis cuts it straight to backward point.
FOUR! Poor delivery. Darted this down leg side. Dinesh Chandimal steps out and tries to flick it but gets a thin edge and it goes past the keeper for a boundary.
Tossed up outside off, defended well.
Flatter on leg, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it out of his front foot.
Leg break on middle, Dinesh Chandimal negotiates it well.
On off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up on middle and leg, this is flicked towards square leg for one.
A low full toss outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it towards covers for one.
Goes fuller and on middle, Ramesh Mendis awkwardly defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Ramesh Mendis guides it towards mid off.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Ramesh Mendis eases it towards mid on fielder.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Ramesh Mendis flicks it towards the leg side.
Fuller and outside off with a hint of turn, Ramesh Mendis looks to play at it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards gully.
Full-toss down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal drives it wide of long on for a single.
Flatter and quicker outside off, Mendis lets it go to the keeper.
Flatter on middle, turning away. Mendis tries to play it but gets beaten on his outside edge.
Tossed up on middle, Mendis blocks it out to the leg side.
Full and on middle, defended.
Loopy one on leg, Mendis pushes to mid on. Mendis is trying to waste time here by talking to the square leg umpire.
tossed up on middle, turned away sharply. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it.
Floated on off, Chandimal guides it short covers.
Tossed up on middle, turning away. Dinesh Chandimal lets it go to the keeper.
Floated on off, blocked towards covers.
Full and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal eases it to long on for a single.
Loopy delivery outside off, Ramesh Mendis pushes it towards covers. That will be STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Tossed up, around off, hint of spin there. Chandimal tucks it to short leg.
Huge spin this time! This lands outside off, fuller and spins in sharply. Chandimal prods across to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads.
Full ball, outside off. Chandimal sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Mendis stays back to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
This one lands on middle and spins on the pads. Mendis nudges it to square leg.
A loopy ball, outside off. Mendis strides forward and blocks it out.
A length ball, shaping way outside off. Chandimal shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, outside off. Chandimal punches it to deep point for a single.
Better from Starc, targeting the pads! This is on a length. Mendis bunts it away to mid-wicket.
A bouncer now on middle. Mendis sits under it.
Length and around the 5th stump channel. Mendis gets behind the line to block it.
Another bouncer in the over and Mendis evades it well.
Tad short and around off. Chandimal sweeps it straight to short fine leg.
A loopy ball on middle. Chandimal slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Too full and outside off. Mendis skips down and eases it to long on for one more.
FOUR! First boundary of the Day! Tossed up, outside off. Chandimal steps down and across and sweeps it hard to deep square leg where the man dives to his right but fails to stop.

A flatter ball, outside off, this one lands and shoots. Chandimal looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the grills. The ball lobs to the right of short leg. It came off the helmet so a concussion protocal will follow.
Fuller and outside off. Chandimal sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Length and on off. Defended out.
Full and around middle and leg. Chandimal forces it to the right of mid on for a single.
Three runs! Nicely played! Fuller and outside off, angling across. Mendis leans and punches it through covers for three runs.
Bangs a short one, on off. Chandimal lets it go.
Starc gets a hint of shape here, this one jags in, fuller and on middle, it is drilled to mid on.
Short ball to end the over and Chandimal is happy to let it go.
Shorter and outside off, spinning in. Mendis covers his stumps and leaves it.
Floated ball, outside off. Kept out.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! A flighted ball, full and outside off. Mendis uses his feet and hammers it over mid on and it bounces in front of the fence for a boundary.
On off, blocked out.
Quicker, fuller and on middle. Mendis stays back and blocks it.
On middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Floats one full and on middle. Mendis blocks on the leg side.
Flatter and outside off, punched to covers.
Too short and outside off, cut to deep point for one more.

Just past the fielder! Nicely tossed up, full and outside off. Chandimal leans to defend but it spins away and gets the outside edge but rolls past the diving first slip fielder and to short third man for a single.
Full and on middle, worked to mid on for one more.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Mendis steps down the track and defends it towards the leg side with the turn.
Pushed quicker on middle. Mendis works it towards the fine leg region for a single.
Lyon comes 'round the wicket and bowls it flatter on off. Dinesh Chandimal plays it back to the bowler.
Turning into middle. Chandimal works it to mid-wicket this time.
Again the same line on middle. Chandimal nudges it in the gap towards deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up nicely, around off. Mendis skips down the track and pushes it past Lyon as the mid off fielder cuts it off.
Fires it quicker on middle. Chandimal works it towards short mid-wicket.
Tad shorter and around off. Chandimal chops it to backward point.
Lovely delivery, bit of drift on this one on off. Chandimal defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Chandimal forces it to long on for a single.
Quicker delivery at 92 kph, around off. Mendis blocks it off the back foot.
Much fuller on middle. Mendis defends it off the front foot this time.
Lyon with a flatter delivery, around off. Chandimal looks to sweep but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. However, the impact it outside off as the umpire turns down the appeal.

FOUR! This time he connects and gets a boundary! A fuller delivery that drifts on leg. Chandimal paddles it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up! This is also Chandimal's highest score against the Aussies.
Bit slower through the air on off. Chandimal sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery, on off. Mendis defends it towards the leg side.
Pulls his length back slightly and it turns into middle. Mendis uses the depth of the crease and works it square off the wicket on the leg side.
Goes fuller on off. Menids lets it turns and then blocks it out.
A full toss on middle. Chandimal works it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Nothing much happening for Australia at the moment, they need to pull their socks here. The lead is already 97!
Pushed quicker and almost on a yorker length on off. Mendis blocks it out.
Slower through the air on off. Mendis looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards the backward point fielder.
Tossed up on middle. Mendis reaches the pitch of the ball and works it towards mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on middle. Menids drives it to mid on.
Single to end the over! A fuller one on middle. Mendis works it nicely wide of mid on for a single.
Flighted delivery, around off. Mendis blocks it off the front foot.
Tosses this up, around off at 83 kph. Mendis skips down the track and works it to wide of long on for a single.

Only Marnus Labuschagne is interested there, a loud appeal from him for an LBW! This is outside off and tossed up. Chandimal looks to reverse-sweep it but misses. The ball hits his pads and the impact is outside off.
On off and fuller. Chandimal flicks it right of the bowler.
Gives it a bit of flight on off. Chandimal skips down the track and pushes it to long on for a single.
On the shorter side, around off. Mendis punches it to covers for a single.
Tossed up on leg, Mendis knocks it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, blocked towards the bowler.
Full and on middle, turning away. Mendis pushes it to the off side.
A bit short outside off, turning away. Mnedis cuts it from his back foot towards point for a run.
Tossed up on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it straight to short extra cover.
Full-toss on middle, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards long on for a single.
Starts with a full-toss on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it through covers for a run.
Flatter on middle, turning away sharply. Mendis knocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Mendis flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
A bit short and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal cuts it straight to backward point.
Similar to the previous delivery, Dinesh Chandimal this time cuts it to the right of point and gets the single.
Short again on middle and off, Mendis slaps it to long on for one.
Full-toss drifting down the leg, Mendis flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls the full-toss again on middle, Dinesh Chandimal drives it to mid off for a single.
Slower through the air on middle, Mendis digs it towards mid on.
Tossed up on middle,turning away. Mendis leaves it alone.

Floated on middle, Mendis tries to flick it but it goes straight to short leg. They appeal for the catch but the finger stays down. The umpire goes upstairs and the replay shows the ball bounced before going to the fielder.

Flatter and quicker on leg, Mendis tries to play at it but gets hit on the pads. Shouts for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Perhaps it was going down the leg side. Actually, the replay shows it was going onto hit the stumps. But unfortunately Australia do not have a review. Mitchell Marsh from the pavilion indicates the same during the break.
Floated on leg, turning a bit. Dinesh Chandimal works it through mid wicket for a single.
Tossed up on off, Mendis defends it to the off side.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Mendis leans on and blocks it out.
Full-toss on middle, Dinesh Chandimal smacks it but straight to mid-wicket.
Nice delivery. Slower through the air on middle, turning away. Mendis tries to block it but gets an outside edge and the ball runs towards third man. They get two runs.
Short and wide on off, Mendis pulls it to long on for one.

OUT! LBW! What a start by Mitchell Starc. The new ball does the trick and Australia break this partnership. Mitchell Starc bowls this full on middle, swinging in late. Mendis tries to play at it but gets beaten all ends up and was caught plumb in front. It looks so beautiful on the replay. A lovely inswing-yorker from Starc. Australia had to wait a bit to break the stand and they will now look to take remaining wickets quickly.
Almost action replay. Bowls it full again,swinging in. Maheesh Theekshana misses the ball and gets hit on his pads. It was going down.
On a length outside off, angling away, Maheesh Theekshana throws his bat but it just misses his outside edge. Mitchell Marsh looking really good.
Full and outside off, Maheesh Theekshana goes for the drive but could not connect.
An inswinger from Starc on middle and leg, Maheesh Theekshana digs it out to mid on.

NOT OUT! Mitchell Starc bowls it on a length outside off, Maheesh Theekshana tries to drive at it but misses it. The Aussie's appeal for a caught behind and up goes the finger. Maheesh Theekshana does not think that he has nicked this one and takes the review after consulting his partner. The Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat involved. So, the decision will be overturned and Maheesh Theekshana survives and Sri Lanka keep their review.
Flatter and outside off. Chandimal punches it to covers for a single. So, Chandimal is trusting Maheesh Theekshana with the bat. Let's see how it goes.

FOUR! Takes the charge! Tossed up, outside off. Theekshana comes down the track and looks to go over covers but does not connect it well. He does well to clear mid off and the ball races into the fence.
Flatter and around off. Theekshana skips down and fends it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and spinning on middle. Theekshana hangs back to block it to mid-wicket. A single.
FOUR! Second one! Shorter and way outside off. Chandimal gets time to punch it through point for a boundary.
This one slides down the leg side. Chandimal fails to flick it away.
A length ball, sliding on the pads. Theekshana keeps it out.
A short one, angling outside off. Theekshana is not tempted to play at it.
Pushes it through outside off. Theekshana tries to drive but misses.
Tight from Starc! Short of a length, around off. Theekshana thinks to defend but pulls his bat out late.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Theekshana nudges it to square leg for a single.
Bye! A loosener! Full and down the leg side. Chandimal fails to flick it away and it rolls to fine leg for a bye.
On middle, blocked out.
Shorter and on middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter and spinning around off. Theekshana dances down the track and blocks it out.
Length and angling on middle. Theekshana again blocks it out.
Tossed up, around off, spinning in. Theekshana prods to defend but gets hit on the pads. It lobs over keeper but the batters don't cross.
Slanting on middle, tucked to short leg. Theekshana survives the over.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to covers.
Full again, outside off, this one nips away. Chandimal looks to drive away from the body but misses.
A yorker, swinging on off. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it out quickly.
Fuller ball, worked to covers for a single.
Starc tries to swing back in but fails and this goes with the angle outside off. Theekshana looks to drive but misses.
Effort ball from Strac but Theekshana covers it up! A yorker, swinging in, on middle. Theekshana somehow bocks it. Starc throws some words to Theekshana.
