150 for Dinesh Chandimal! Excellent from him! He has taken his team to a very good position here. It has been a brilliant innings from him! A shorter ball on off. He pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, angling around off, it nips away off the deck. Theekshana looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. The ball is inches away from hitting the off pole.
Length and outside off, it is hit to covers.
FOUR! Theekshana won't mind it! A length ball, outside off. Theekshana opens the face of the bat and guides it to the right of first slip who watches it race into the third man fence.
Shorter and on middle. Theekshana sits under it.
Fuller and on off. Theekshana blocks it out.
Starc lands it short and outside off. Chandimal cuts it to sweeper cover. However, he does not take a single this time.
Lands on a length, swinging into Chandimal at 140 kph. Chandimal hops and looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a stifled appeal but nothing serious.
Back of a length, around off. Chandimal stands tall and punches it to covers.
Takes a single this time. A shorter-length delivery, around off. Chandimal pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Maheesh Theekshana has to survive two deliveries now.
Bangs it short and around leg. Maheesh Theekshana ducks under it.

Brilliant delivery but equally well played by Maheesh Theekshana! Starc comes charging in from 'round the wicket and spears in a yorker on middle and leg. Maheesh Theekshana though gets his bat down in time.
Lands on a length, around off. Chandimal looks to push it away but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Serves it on a length again, on off at 133 kph. Chandimal knocks it back to the bowler.
Bangs it short but at comfortable height for Chandimal. He pulls it to deep square leg for a single. Three balls remaining in this over, can Maheesh Theekshana survive?

OUT! BOWLED! No, he can't! Pat Cummins destroys the off stump and gets his first wicket of this Test match! Cummins with a good-length delivery, on off. The ball nips away a bit after pitching and beats the forward defence of Maheesh Theekshana. It knocks over the off pole and Maheesh Theekshana after playing a gritty little knock, walks back to the pavilion. Can Australia wrap this innings up quickly now?
Goes a tad fuller on off. Prabath Jayasuriya keeps it out.
Lands on a length and it is outside off. Prabath Jayasuriya defends it inside the line of the ball as the ball goes back to the keeper.
Back of a length, on middle at 138 kph. Chandimal stays back and defends it towards the leg side.

This is full and outside off. Chandimal throws his bat at it. However, he gets a thick outside edge that flies over the slip fielders. David Warner is very fine at the third man region and stops it. No single taken.
Back of a length and around off. Chandimal defends it towards the off side.
On the shorter side on off. Chandimal backs away a bit and swings hard but only gets the bottom of his blade as the ball goes back to the bowler.
Lands it a tad short again, around off. Chandimal slaps it without much timing to long off for a single.
Starc goes for a yorker. However, the length is right but the line is not as it is outside off. Prabath Jayasuriya looks to dig it out but misses. Sri Lanka are 499/8 at Lunch on Day 4!
Takes a single off the first delivery of the over! 500 up for Sri Lanka! Back of a length, around off. Chandimal punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Cummins bangs it short on middle and leg. Prabath Jayasuriya ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Prabath Jayasuriya with a solid block from his crease.
Goes fuller on off. Prabath Jayasuriya drives it to the cover region.
On the shorter side on middle. Prabath Jayasuriya blocks it out. No signs of aggression from Lanka so far.
Keeps it a tad short on off. Prabath Jayasuriya defends it solidly off the back foot.
FOUR! Dinesh Chandimal strikes it firmly and gets a boundary! This is full on middle. Chandimal backs away a bit and drives it straight down the ground for a boundary.
A fullish delivery on middle. Chandimal swings but gets the bottom of his blade to long on. He denies a single this time.
Starc keeps it full on middle at 128 kph. Chandimal blocks it out.
Lands on a length, on off. Chandimal drives it to sweeper cover and takes a single.

OUT! BOWLED! Mitchell Starc cleans him up with a trademark yorker! He comes 'round the wicket and nails a yorker on off. It is too good for Prabath Jayasuriya as he misses it while trying to block it away. The off stump is uprooted and Starc gets his fourth wicket and the lead is now 141. How many more can Sri Lanka get?
FOUR! Well controlled shot. This is short and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal pulls it hard towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Well controlled shot. This is short and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal pulls it hard towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
On a length on middle, defended down the pitch.
Good length on top of off stump, Dinesh Chandimal blocks it of his front foot.
Full and down the leg side, Dinesh Chandimal glances it down to fine leg and gets a brace.
SIX! The runs are flowing now. Bangs it short outside off, Dinesh Chandimal makes room and heaves it over covers for a biggie. The lead goes past 150 now.
Wide! Good cricket from Sri Lanka. This is on a length way outside off, Dinesh Chandimal offers no shot at it. They run a quick bye and its called a wide too.
Good length and outside off, Kasun Rajitha guides it to third man of his outside edge. They don't take the single.
Full and down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards deep mid-wicket.
FOUR! Poor delivery. Back of a length down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal tickles it past the keeper for another boundary.
SIX! That is huge. Starc goes full and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal heaves it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Full again on leg, Dinesh Chandimal smashes it to wide of long on but refuses the single,
This time he takes the single. Full and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal drills it towards long on for a run.
Kasun Rajitha survives. This is a yorker on middle, angling in. Kasun Rajitha digs it out well.
Back of a length on middle and leg, slower too. Dinesh Chandimal pulls it to deep square leg.
This is full and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through square leg but denies the run.
On a length down the leg, Dinesh Chandimal guides it to fine leg. But again does not take the single.
Good length on middle and leg, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it with soft hands through mid-wicket and gets a brace.
Bangs it short on middle, angling in. Dinesh Chandimal awkwardly pulls it to the leg side and calls for two, but decides against it, They get one.
That was close. Pat Cummins bowls it full and on leg, Kasun Rajitha moves across and tries to play the flick but misses and it goes just past the leg stump.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Chandimal. Starc bowls a full toss on leg, Dinesh Chandimal picks this off and smashes it towards deep square leg fence for another boundary.

SIX! Massive hit. This is full and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal hits it through the line and heavs it over long on for a huge six. Moves to 195 now. This is the highest individual score by a Lankan against Australia.

SIX! 200 up for Chandimal. What a way to get to your maiden double century. This is full and in the slot on leg, Dinesh Chandimal clears his back leg and lofts it over the deep mid-wicket fence for another biggie. This has been an incredible innings by him. The crowd in on their feet as they appreciate this magnificient innings.
Full toss on off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it through extra cover.
Too full and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal digs it towards third man for a single.
This is not gonna trouble Kasun Rajitha. Starc bowls it full and way outside leg. Kasun Rajitha is happy to let go and Alex Carey does well to stop that diving to his left.
Full and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal knocks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it down the pitch.
On a length and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal guides it to deep backward point. He denies the single again.
Pulls back his length again on off, slower too. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it towards point and takes the single.
Full and on middle, angling in. Kasun Rajitha knocks it mid on.
On a length and on middle, Kasun Rajitha defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off. Chandimal blocks it on the off side.
Fuller and outside off, turning away. Left alone.
Two! Fuller and on off. Chandimal pushes it to deep extra cover and takes two easily.
Flatter and on off. Chandimal pushes it to covers for a single. Trusting Kasun Rajitha now.
Tossed up on off. Kasun Rajitha blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! LBW! Finally, Sri Lanka are dismissed on 554. Tossed up, around off, it spins in. Kasun Rajitha gets on the front foot but defends the wrong line. He gets rapped on the pads and the umpire raises his finger after the appeal. Kasun Rajitha reviews it but that was plumb. The decision stays and Sri Lanka end with a lead of 190 runs.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off, swings away late. Warner looks to slash at it but misses.
Fuller ball on off. Warner solidly defends on the front foot.
On a length, nipping back in around off. Warner blocks it on the deck.
Shapes a length ball, around off. Warner covers his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
This one straightens up, length and outside off. David shoulders arms again.
So, a maiden to start the proceedings! A length ball, just outside off. Warner blocks it out.
Fuller and angling on the pads. Khawaja seems to get an inside edge there as he looks to flick and the ball lobs to the right of short leg, well wide of him.
Tossed up on middle. Khawaja flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs. Australia and Usman Khawaja are underway!
Fuller and on off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, defended out.

Bye! How has that missed the stumps! Nicely flighted, full and on leg. The ball spins away and goes past the off pole. Khawaja was off-balance so there is a stumping chance as well. The keeper fails to collect. A bye taken!
On middle, blocked out.
On a length and on off. Khawaja defends it on the deck.
Length and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Khawaja punches it through point for a single.
Angling on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Fullish length, on off. Warner gets a straight bat down and pushes it to mid n.
On middle on a length. Defended out.
Slanting full, around middle and leg. Khawaja fends it to short leg.
Floated on off. Khawaja takes the charge but does not reach to the pitch of the ball well. Hits it to mid on.
FOUR! First boundary of the innings! Tossed up, drifting on middle. Khawaja paddles it firmly through fine leg for a boundary.
Flatter and outside off. Blocked out.
Tries a leggie but no spin there, outside off. Khawaja keeps it out.
Tossed up on off. Khawaja hangs on the back foot to block it.
On a length and on off. Warner guides it to covers.
On off, kept out.
Good delivery! Slants a full ball on middle. Warner is right behind the line to defend it.
Too full and on off. David drills it to mid off, straight to the man there.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length on the hips. Warner turns it to mid-wicket for a single.
A flatter one on middle. Warner defends it from his crease.
Sliding into leg. Warner looks to clip it but misses and gets hit high on his back leg.
Sligthly slower through the air, on off. Warner pushes it gently to covers for a single.
Slider again on off at 91 kph. Usman Khawaja blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Quality shot! Maheesh Theekshana goes fuller on leg. Usman Khawaja skips down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and flicks it aerially towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Goes fuller on off. Usman Khawaja drives it to covers this time.
Back of a length, on off. Warner dabs it towards cover-point for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played again by Usman Khawaja! Short and outside off. Usman Khawaja rides the bounce and punches it through backward point for a boundary.
On the shorter side again, on leg. Usman Khawaja pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Serves a good-length delivery, around off. Warner leaves it alone.
Lands it on a length again, outside off. Warner makes a good leave again. Australian openers are looking pretty comfortable so far, maybe it is time for a bowling change.

Ohh...good sharp reflexes by Kasun Rajitha! This is fuller on off. Warner drives it back to the bowler. Kasun Rajitha collects it and fires a direct hit at the batter's end. Warner is quite alert as well and dives back to make his crease. The umpire takes it upstairs and the replays show that Warner is back in the crease.
A fuller delivery on middle. Usman Khawaja works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Pushed quicker on off. Warner again drives it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Great use of the feet! On middle. Warner shimmies down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and just lifts it over mid on for a boundary.
Better from Maheesh Theekshana! A bit of drift on this one. He pushes it quicker on middle. Warner goes back and blocks it out.
FOUR! Clever from Warner! A full toss on middle. Warner just paddles it to the fine leg fence for a boundary. This has been a good positive start from the Aussies.
Slower through the air on middle. Warner knocks it down to long on for a single.
Lands on a length, on middle from 'round the wicket. Warner defends it off the front foot.
Goes tad fuller on off at 135 kph. Warner pushes it to mid off.
Serves it on a length angling into middle from wide of the crease. Warner though blocks it out calmly.
FOUR! Nicely timed! The outfield gives you full value. Overpitched delivery on off. Warner leans forward and drives it in the gap beautifully between mid off and the cover fielder.
Kasun Rajitha pulls his length back, on off at 133 kph. Warner is right behind it to block it.

FOUR! Boundaries are flowing now for Australia! Short and wide outside off. Warner cuts it in front of square through covers for a boundary. Warner comes nicely on the top of this delivery and creams it away.
Tossed up on middle. Usman Khawaja forces it back to the bowler.
Nicely bowled! Slower through the air on middle. Usman Khawaja looks to defend it off the front foot. He does that but off the outside half of his blade.
Goes very full on middle. Usman Khawaja drives it off the bottom of his blade back to the bowler.
On the shorter side and angling into leg. Usman Khawaja looks to work it towards the leg side but gets not timing on this one.
Keeps it a tad short sliding into middle and leg. Usman Khawaja works it towards the leg side.
Flighted delivery on off. Usman Khawaja with a solid block off the front foot.
Starts with a loopy delivery on middle, Warner blocks it to the off side.
Full and on leg, Warner goes down and sweeps it through backward square leg for a single.
A bit short on middle and leg, Usman Khawaja tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, turning a bit down the leg. Khawaja tries to flick but misses.
Well Bowled! Slower through the air on off, Khawaja blocks it well.
Full and on off, Khawaja drives it to short extra cover.
Loopy delivery on middle, Warner defends it well.
A bit short on off, drifting away. Warner pushes it to the off side.
Tossed up on off, Warner uses his feet and punches to point for one.
Floated on middle, blocked out.
FOUR! Nice shot! This is slightly shorter on middle, Usman Khawaja pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Short again outside off, Usman Khawaja cuts it through point for a run.
Too full on middle, Usman Khawaja drives it long on for a single.
Tossed up on off, Warner comes down the pitch to defend it.
Slower through the air outside off, Warner knocks it to the off side.
Floated on middle, Warner goes down and sweeps it to backward square leg for a single.
Flatter and quicker on leg, Khawaja drills it past silly mid on for another run.
Tossed up on off from 'round the wicket, Warner plays the reverse sweep towards deep point for a run.

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis gets the breakthrough. This is tossed up on middle, drifting in. David Warner goes for the sweep again but misses the ball completeley and gets rapped on the pads. The Sri Lankans appeal and the finger goes up. David Warner takes the review after consulting with his partner but the Ball Tracking shows three reds and he has to go back. A crucial breakthrough for Sri Lanka, Warner was looking pretty comfortable in the middle but fails to kick on again.
Floated on middle and leg, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it behind sqaure for a run.
Quick Single. Fltatter on off, Khawaja pushes it towards backward point. Marnus Labuschagne calls for the run and they get across.
Slower through the air outside off, spinning in. Marnus Labuschagne comes down the pitch to defend but gets hit on his pads. There is a slight appeal but the umpire is not interested.
A bit short on middle, Marnus Labuschagne works it through square leg for a run.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated on middle, Marnus Labuschagne clips it to short leg.
Tossed up on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it well.
Flatter and quicker on off, angling in. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it of his back foot.
BEATEN! This is tossed up on off, with a hint of turn. Marnus Labuschagne gets rooted to his crease and tries to poke at it but gets beaten on his outside edge.
Fuller and on middle. Blocked out on the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Marnus Labuschagne prods and blocks it out. That will be Tea on Day 4.
Flatter and on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and outside off. Usman Khawaja punches it to deep point for a single.
Tossed up, outside off, stays a bit low. Labuschagne defends it out. The ball was rolling back so he flicks it out.
On middle, tucked straight to square leg.
Fuller and on middle. Labuschagne nudges it straight to short leg.
Fuller and on off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up, outside off. Usman Khawaja gets into the line of the ball to block it.
Flatter and again outside off. Kept out.
Slower, full and angling on middle. Usman Khawaja reverse sweeps it to deep point for a single.
Beautifully bowled! Tossed up on off, it lands and spins away. Labuschagne prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside egde. Perfect line and length that.
Quicker this on middle. Labuschagne tucks it through short leg for a single.
Floated full and on middle. Usman Khawaja goes back to block it.
Fuller and on middle. Labuschagne drills it to wide of mid on for a quick single.
Tossed up on off. Usman Khawaja lunges and defends it out.
Slightly short and on off. Usman Khawaja guides it to point for a single.

Ohh, dear! A misfield helps the batters to settle! Flatter and outside off. Labuschagne punches it to covers. There is a mix up for a quick single but they make the ground as Prabath Jayasuriya fails to pick it up cleanly. Would have been very tight.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for one more.
This one spins sharply onto the pads. Labuschagne waits and tickles it to square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! The spinners are piling the pressure and Usman Khawaja holes one out! Both the openers are gone! Jayasuriya tosses it up, full and on middle, drifting on the pads. Usman Khawaja strides forward to defend but gets an inside edge and Oshada Fernando at short leg dives to his right and takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Oshada Fernando b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Fuller and on middle. Smith plays a front foot defense.
Full and outside off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up on middle. Blocked out.

OUT! LBW! THREE REDS! Prabath Jayasuriya continuing the good work from the first innings! He now has 8 wickets in this match! What a delivery again! This is flatter, length and on middle and off, it spins away after hitting the deck. Steven Smith rocks on the back foot and looks to defend but misses and gets pinged on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW and up goes the finger. Steven Smith walks towards Labuschagne and has a chat. He takes the review. Looks plumb there. No bat there confirms the Ultra Edge. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Smith has to go back. It was more in hope from Smith. The centurion goes for a cheap score this time. Australia in a deep trouble.
Shorter and on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Short, too much width there. Labuschagne punches it hard through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off and spinning in. Labuschagne gets forward to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Shorter and sliding in. Labuschagne keeps it out.
A loopy ball, outside off. Labuschagne reaches to the pitch of the ball to defend it.
FOUR! Just as we saw on the first ball of this over! Shorter and width there. Labuschagne punches it through covers for a boundary.
Shorter, stays low outside off. Labuschagne pushes it to point and keeps the strike.
Nicely bowled, tossed up on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Goes fuller on middle. Marnus Labuschagne sweeps it firmly towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep moves to left and dives to make a good stop. A single taken.
FOUR! Nicely played! Prabath Jayasuriya bowls it fuller on off. Head gets a bit across and sweeps it with the turn towards the square leg fence for a boundary.
Playing the sweep-shot with the turn again. On middle this time and Head hits it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Tad shorter and flatter on middle. Marnus Labuschagne goes deep in his crease and defends it towards the leg side.
Slower through the air on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! What a delivery and Sri Lanka are right on top here! This is a lovely delivery that pitches on middle and then grips. A classic off-spinner's delivery. Head goes back and looks to defend. The ball turns away and knocks over his off pole. The crowd erupts and Australia are in all sorts of trouble here.
Tossed up on off. Green drives it to mid off.
A fuller delivery on off. Green drives it to covers for a single.
Flighted delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne reaches the pitch of the ball and drives it to covers.
Pulls his length back a bit on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
Turning into middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up on middle. Marnus Labuschagne sweeps and sweeps well in front of square for a boundary.
Slower through the air on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
An arm ball on middle. Marnus Labuschagne does well to defend it.
Angling into middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
This is fuller on middle. Green skips down the track and drives it to mid off. Takes a quick single.
Sliding into middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to short fine leg. Oshada Fernando collects it quickly and throws it back towards the stumps.
Shorter and outside off. Green punches it through covers for a single.
Pushed quicker on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the back foot.
Turning into middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it towards backward square leg.
Slightly quicker on middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for a single.
Mendis changes the angle as he comes 'round the wicket. It is on middle. Green skips down the track and defends it.
FOUR! SHOT! Overpitched, around off. Green recahes the pitch of the ball with a big stride and drives it past mid off for a boundary.
Flatter and angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air on off. Marnus Labuschagne charges down thye track and defends it.
Angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Pushed quicker on middle. Green blocks it off the back foot.
Ohh..just past the outside edge! Tad shorter and turning away from around off. Green goes back and looks to cut but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
On the shorter side, around off. Green punches it to covers this time.

TURN AND BOUNCE! This is tossed up on off, turning in sharply. Marnus Labuschagne goes to play at it but gets beaten by the turn and bounce and it hits him high on his body. The fielder at short fine leg catches it and the Lankan players make an appeal. However, the umpire turns it down. No review taken by Sri Lanka as well.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated on middle, Marnus Labuschagne tucks it backward square and gets across for a quick single.
Full and outside off, Green drives it to long off for a run.
Full again outside off, Marnus Labuschagne steps out and works it through mid on for a single.
Tossed up on off, Green comes down the pitch and blocks it out.
Floated on off, Marnus Labuschagne sweeps it through mid-wicket for a run.
Floated on middle and leg, Green leans forward and defends it to the leg side.
Short and on middle and leg, Green goes back in his crease and pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Full and outside off, Green drives it straight to covers.
FOUR! Top class shot! Tossed up on middle, Green steps out and drills it over the bowler for a boundary.
Floated on leg, Green works it to mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up outside off, turning in. Green blocks it of his back foot.
On middle, defended out.
Tossed up outside off, Green gets to the pitch of the ball and knocks it back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, Green punches of his back foot through covers for a run.
Floated on middlle, Marnus Labuschagne plays a front foot defense.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Marnus Labuschagne leans on and blocks it back to the bowler.
Too full on middle, Green drives it towards long on for a single.
Floated on middle, Marnus Labuschagne uses his feet and defends it to the off side.
Slower through the air, turning away a bit. Marnus Labuschagne goes for the drive but gets a thin outside edge and the ball rolls towards third man. They cross.
Floated outside off, Green kncoks it straight to mid off.
A bit short outside off, Green punches it through covers for a couple of runs.
Tossed up on middle, Green blocks it down the pitch.
Too full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne digs it to mid off for a quick single.
Floated on middle, Green defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, turning in sharply. Green uses his feet to get to the pitch of the ball but misses and gets hit on his body.
Full again outside off, Green drives against the turn towards long off for a single.
Short and on leg, Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to backward square.
Too short again on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it in front of square for another single.
Very full and on middle, swept behind square on the leg side for a single.
Fuller and on middle. Green skips down and pushes it to long off for a single.
Slower, flatter and on off. Labuschagne rocks back to defend.
Fuller and outside off. Labuschagne sweeps it hard through mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep runs to his left, dives and saves two.
On middle, blocked out.

OUT! LBW! Prabath Jayasuriya strikes again! What a match he is having! A dream debut! This is flighted, very full and around off. Labuschagne looks to sweep but gets decieved in the flight, he gets rapped on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW and up goes the finger. Labuschagne knows he is out but still walks towards Green and tries to convince himself but gets the same answer from his partner. That is plumb in front. Out it is! The replay later shows three reds!
Tossed up on off, pushed to long off for a single.
A full toss on middle, eased to mid on for a single.
Spinning on the pads. Green flicks it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off. Carey blocks it on the front foot.
Full ball on middle. Carey looks to flick but gets an inside edge to square leg. Short leg there standing and it could be easily out.
On middle, kept out.
This is full. Carey sweeps it from outside off, uppishly and to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! STUMPED! Prabath Jayasuriya gets his fourth and 10th wicket overall in this match! What a game he is having! Truly magical! Another flighted delivery, it lands on leg and spins away sharply. Cameron Green comes down the track to push at it but gets beaten and Niroshan Dickwella does really well to collect it and clip the bails off before Green can comes back in. He tries to but till then the bails were dislodged. Australia 6 down and are into the lower orders now. Still trailing by 73 runs.
Howout: st Niroshan Dickwella b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: On middle, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Prabath Jayasuriya gets another one to his name! He already has two five-wickets hauls now! What a debut! Jayasuriya tosses it up, full and outside off, it turns in. Starc takes a big stride forward to defend but does so in the wrong line, he gets an outside edge and Kusal Mendis dives to his right at first slip and takes a brilliant catch. That was really sharp from Mendis.
Howout: c Kusal Mendis b Prabath Jayasuriya

Commentary: Shorter and outside off, spinning away. Cummins is beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend.
Outside off again, touch fuller. Cummins looks to push but misses again.
Full and on middle. Carey flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On middle, blocked out.
A loopy ball on off. Alex keeps it out.
Flatter and outside off. Carey rocks back and blocks it.
On off, kept out.
Mendis needs to keep tight from this end also! He is so far a bit wayward! Shorter and outside off. Carey cuts it to deep point for a single.
Tossed up, outside off, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Too full, flighted and on middle. Pat Cummins first thinks to heave it but forces it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller ball on off. Carey sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Too full and angling on middle. Pat Cummins this time sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
A fuller delivery on off. Carey defends it off the front foot.
SIX! Just over! Floated, full and on middle. Pat Cummins gets on his knee and slog-sweeps it over cow corner for a biggie. There was a fielder but he was a mere spectator.
Tossed up on off. Carey defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air on off. Carey with a front foot defence again.
Pushed it bit fuller on middle. Carey looks to clip it towards the leg side but gets a leading edge towards covers.
Nice loopy delivery on middle. Carey is again on the front foot to defend it.
Pushes it a tad quicker and around off. Carey stays back and blocks it.
Pitched on middle and it turns and bounces. However, Carey manages to defend it out.
Tossed up on middle. Cummins looks to slog-sweep it but gets no timing here.

FOUR! Edge but just past Kusal Mendis at first slip! On the shorter side and quicker, around off. Cummins looks to punch it away. The ball catches the outside edge and goes between the slip fielder and keeper. It races away towards the third man fence.
Tossed up on middle. Cummins pushes it towards the leg side for a single.
Fires it on middle. Carey reverse-sweeps it to backward point for a single.
Flatter and quicker around off. Cummins lets it go.

Slower through the air on off. Cummins goes for the slog-sweep. However, the connection is not good enough and the ball goes aerially and falls short of the fielder at deep mid-wicket. A single taken.
Tad shorter, around off. Cummins goes back and defends it towards the off side for a single.
A full toss on middle. Carey flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. While Prabath Jayasuriya has been very good with his control, Mendis on the other hand has been a bit wayward.
Pushed quicker on off. Cummins blocks it out.
Shorter in length but down the leg side. Cummins looks to pull it but misses.
Much better. Nice loopy delivery on off. Cummins comes forward and defends it out.
Slower through the air on middle. Cummins blocks it yet again.
A very full delivery on off. Carey reverse-sweeps it off the bounce towards first slip.
On middle and Carey just turns it away with spin towards square leg for a single.
A fuller delivery on off. Cummins sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Prabath Jayasuriya goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and bowls it full on off. Carey drives it back to the bowler.
Very full, around off. Carey reverse-sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Slower through the air and around off. Cummins watches it till the end as he lets it go.
Shorter in length, on off. Carey works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! LBW! Maheesh Theekshana comes back into the attack and strikes straight away!  Sri Lanka are just two wickets away now from a huge victory! Maheesh Theekshana with a flatter delivery on middle. It is probably a carrom ball that just turns away a bit after pitching. Cummins looks to defend it but ends up playing through the wrong line. The ball hits his pads and after a big appeal, the umpire raises his finger! Cummins though goes for a review but it does not make any difference as the Ball Tracking shows that the impact and wicket's hitting is umpire's call. So the original decision stays and Cummins has to walk back.
FOUR! Starts off with a boundary! On middle. Lyon sweeps and sweeps it well through backward square leg for a boundary.
On middle. Lyon sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Carey works it towards the leg side for a single.

OUT! LBW! Maheesh Theekshana has another and Lyon who started off with a boundary playing a sweep shot, walks back trying to repeat the same shot again. This is fuller on middle. Lyon goes for a big sweep-shot but misses. The ball again turns slightly away and hits Lyon on his pads. An appeal is entertained again as the umpire raises his finger. He reviews it but the Ball Tracking shows three reds and Australia lose nine now. Just a wicket away Lanka from a famous victory here! Mitchell Swepson is the last man in.
Flatter and full on middle, Carey sweeps it wide of fine leg for a run.
Pulls back his lenght a bit on middle, Swepson blocks it out.
Oh! That was close. Prabath Jayasuriya bowls it full around off, turning away sharply. Swepson goes for the drive but misses it completely.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Tossed up on middle, drifting away. Swepson tries to defends but is beaten all ends up.
Floated outside off, Swepson pushes this to the offside.

OUT! BOWLED! It's all over! Prabath Jayasuriya has his 12th wicket in the game and what a turnaround this has been from Sri Lanka! This is tossed up on middle and Mitchell Swepson tries to defend it off the back foot. However, Prabath Jayasuriya gets that turn again by which he has been troubling Aussies throughout this Test match. The ball beats the outside edge of Mitchell Swepson's blade and knocks over the off pole. Sri Lanka win by an innings and 39 runs.
